description:
Materia
‘Atlas:Remixed’
(Slime Recordings)
Cat # SLM090

Slime Recordings reached a new milestone this year with the launch of its first physical release – the debut album from Swedish producer Materia. ‘Atlas’ was the result - an album that extrapolates the fundamentals of house, garage, dubstep and techno - then fuses them into a listening experience full of warmth and texture which reveals further depths through every repeated play. The album garnered a lot of accolades, with Igloo Magazine calling it “a genuine work of substance” and Electronic Music Magazine describing it as “immensely satisfying”.

To celebrate the success of the release, Slime has commissioned six producers to remix some of the key tracks on the album. The result is an intriguing selection from some of the most creative underground producers working today.

First up we welcome Submerse back to the label. One of the most talented producers around, here he develops on the sound he has been cultivating on his Project:Mooncircle releases with a slow motion version of the lead track from the album, ‘Otherland’. Extrapolating all the original elements of the track and twisting them into something completely new and refreshing, it’s clear to see why he is so highly regarded as an artist.

‘Otherland’ is taken into another direction by the legendary drum & bass producer Macc, who we have managed to coax out of retirement to tackle this remix. The original’s ethereal qualities are kept intact, but infused with truly astounding drum work and delicate melodies reconstructed with pin-sharp clarity for a mix that is truly special.

For the final remix of the lead track, Dublin-based producer Genetix twists the original into a shuffling deep dubstep roller replete with sparkling synths and cavernous low-end that will rattle chests and elevate minds.

Next up, Bristol-based producer Lojik takes on ‘Clouds’. One of the stand-out tracks from the original release, it’s staccato downbeat rhythm is finessed into a bass-heavy groove with superb bars from Bristol MC Koast driving the beat forward alongside the sublime vocals of New York vocalist Winter.

Swedish producer Petter B takes on the closing track from the album, ‘Synthesis’. The Drumcode artist manipulates the spaced-out style of the original into a rolling techno stomper where sparkling melodies are strapped to a heavy-duty groove with devastating results.

Completing the set Bristol-based producer Discord takes ‘Synthesis’ into altogether darker territory with a throbbing techno jam complete with acidic licks and snapping percussion that continually builds until the dancefloor will be in a frenzy.

Available from 07/10/2013 at Juno Download and 14/10/2013 from all good digital stockists.

FFI : www.slimerecordings.co.uk

Mastered by Bob Macc at SC Mastering
Design by Slime
Distributed by Cargo

Tracklisting:

1.Otherland (Submerse Mix)
2.Otherland (Macc Mix)
3.Otherland (Genetix Mix)
4.Clouds (Lojik Mix)
5.Synthesis (Petter B Mix)
6.Synthesis (Discord Mix)

description:
Outlaw welcomes Tm Shuffle on its roster with his 'Waterside Dubs' EP.

Hailing from the forest of Ruutana in Finland, Vuo Records founder TM Shuffle has
been deliver his twist on contemporary dubbed out house and techno over the past years via imprint’s like Roger Gerressen’s Irenic, Translucent, Ranges and of course his own Vuo.
Here though we see him deliver his latest three-track EP via Outlaw, leading the release is ‘Viislampi Dub’ which sees the Finish artist employ classic dub tropes such a fluttering stab sequences and a choppy sub hits alongside a subtly nuanced drum groove.
‘Viimsi’ follows next to open the flip-side, this time round laying focus on hazy pads, bumpy off-kilter percussion and jazzy synth melodies before ‘Nocturnal Dub’ rounds out the release on a stripped-back tip. Employing an amalgamation of sharp synth flutters which ebb and flow around one another amongst a minimalistic, swinging rhythm and expansive echoes.
tag_list: Techno dub minimal Deep dubtechno Outlaw "Matthewo Oh" "Tm Shuffle"
title: TM Shuffle - Waterside Dubs EP [Outlaw008]

description:
OHM & Octal Industries deliver their ‘Chaos Games’ EP via Italian imprint Outlaw this February, comprising three originals from the duo.

Ohm & Octal Industries have been steadily making their mark on the deep and dub
leaning Techno world over the past five years, racking up releases on the likes of
Rawax, Andrey Pushkarev’s Luck Of Access, Nilla and of Thule Records amongst
others. Here though we see the pair joining the roster of Outlaw, the Italian imprint run

by producer, DJ and Matthew Oh.

Kicking off the release is ‘Breather’, an apt name for the composition which attains an
underlying sense of calm via fluttering dub echoes, ethereal atmospherics and
wandering low-end tones while dynamic drums add the dance floor drive.
‘Strange Attractions’ follows next, edging into darker realms via murky synth textures,
squelching 303 licks and thunderous subs before ‘Creation’ rounds out the release,
stripping things back to bumpy shuffled drums, sweeping stab sequences and dubbed

out spoken word vocals.
tag_list: ohm "octal industries" "matthew oh" Outlaw Dub Techno "Dub techno" Chords Vocal Stab 303 Vinyl
title: Ohm & Octal Industries - Chaos Game

“Technoburlesque: Image Snatchers EP” is based on a series of club evenings of the same name created in 2013 by The Feminalz: Tristan Bargeld, Mathilde Buns, H.P.D. (hormonal perturbator in decay), Mad Jakale, Frau Strapatz, Crucial Pink, and guests. For such a variete show, that contained dance, singing, acting and improvisation in parts, with a comical and criticial bend number of electronic musical fragments and reworked reappropriated recordings were written and produced. While the series continues in 2014 and onwards with new noise eruptions and electronic remixes Nova deViator gathered sound fragments for this EP and additionally upgraded and reworked them.

description:
Here we are with the second release of the JUDAS HOLE trilogy: THE SOBER EP includes songs and soundscapes which did not fit on the album, but arrange themselves in an expedient way as a self-contained EP…

With the open-source-release of the first album “TODAY IS SUNDAY” on WM Recordings in 2008 MeanwhileProject.Ltd first started as a one-man-project. In the last three years the album was spread over the internet and reached about 30.000 listeners all over the world where it found general approval. The production of the JOEY BURNS EP and the forthcoming album took place with the support of Music Producer Hannes Jackl from AMPERSAND and features musicians and singers from the bands SCHMACKES UND PINSCHER, MOUTH, LUNATIC SKYDANCE and THE LO-FI FAIR.

The release of the new album THE JUDAS HOLE (including 10 brand-new tracks) will follow later in 2011. With the interlude “Earwalk” the EP contains another track of the new album.

description:
AUDIOTOTEMPOLE 
available from Bandcamp → https://qburns.bandcamp.com/album/audiototempole (name your price)
------------------
Q-Burns Abstract Message is an expert time traveler. But it’s not about the physical transportation of bodies into the past or future. Instead, these are sonic waves, vibrating in all directions, touching different eras and territories. Like a Stalker entering ‘The Zone,’ Q-BAM is forever in search of the undefinable. He’ll know it when he sees it, and today it’s looking like an AUDIOTOTEMPOLE.

M. Donaldson is Q-Burns Abstract Message, formerly broadcasting with Astralwerks and a handful of other co-conspirators. Over the decades he’s wielded turntables in locales from Novosibirsk to Antofagasta, but now he’s mostly quiet. Occasionally Q-Burns Abstract Message pops up in someone’s mix set, or mentioned in a blog post, or perhaps in an odd remix. But, for the most part, he’s a known unknown.

Now he’s reappeared, clutching an AUDIOTOTEMPOLE. It’s an homage to a secret history without the stain of nostalgia. These are songs spanning the lost years, buzzing with electricity and ritual ambiguity. “Tremble,” for example, is handed down from clouds, signaling Q-BAM’s transition from mystic to mystical. “Kept in a Shadehouse” undulates in continuous motion, brightly placing tones in orbit around its bristling center. And “Touchtones (1997)” is an earthy clue, creating the temporal connection — past meets present, full circle.

description:
Solarism is the result of a common fascination for landscapes and a passion for contemplation.

After two decades of an unbreakable friendship, we have finaly imaginated this protean entity to express what contemplation has offered us and how it connects us to the world, describing those experiences through music compositions, dj performances and welcoming other artists to release their art.

After our strong FRANCK ROGER release TIGER IN THE HOOD, we are really happy to get one of our two label drivers, ARNO E. MATHIEU, back on Solarism. «The Earth Project » is dedicated to planet earth and Arno’s feeling for nature, back in his childhood landscapes.

A1 – TEARS OF THE WHALES is an epic, melodic and hypnotic trip, drived by a strong drum and bass-line groove. 
Directly inspired by the Whales journey, this tune evoke also how much this majestic animal have always been an example of a pacific force. Evolving in the deepness of the oceans and traveling all over the planet, whales are also a symbol of how nature suffers of the impact and polution of consumerism system.

B1 – TERRA describs a melancolic and balearic long overview of Arno E. Mathieu’s chilhood landscape with percussive grooves, strong melodic bass-line and anthemic synth gimics. This new Arno’s track evolves in a tight structured arrangement evoking hills, lands and fields that inspired him for so long… 

Welcome back in SOLARISM !
Remy Rain & Arno E. Mathieu

Tracklisting:
A1: Tears Of The Whales – Arno E. Mathieu Original Version   
B1: Terra – Arno E. Mathieu Original Version
tag_list: "ARNO E. MATHIEU" SOLARISM "Deep House" House World
title: ARNO E. MATHIEU - THE EARTH PROJECT

description:
After our first release with Arno E. Mathieu "Existance Project"included Juju & Jordash Rmx, we are really proud to welcome one of our musical friend on Solarism, the non-stop track maker from Home Invasion label, Franck Roger !

On A1 Franck brings a real fusion of Cosmics and classic Deep House vibes, remembering his first love with electronic music but definitely oriented to his nowaday modern vision of sounds. 
The melodic groove of the calimbas percussions drives you till the heart of the track and his swinging drum, to never let you go and brings you up in a neverending hypnotic mind dance. 

On B1, Arno E. Mathieu version push the hypnotic vibe of "Tiger in The Hood" using the original arpegiator theme, and brings the track to a deep techno level for a textured and anthemic experience. Ponctuated by a strings hit appearence and supported by a non stop heavy bass-line, the track progression brings us till a melodic synth conclusion true to Arno fusionned style...

Welcome back in SOLARISM !
Remy Rain & Arno E. Mathieu
title: FRANCK ROGER - TIGER IN THE HOOD - SOLARISM 002
ARNO E MATHIEU - EXISTENCE PROJECT - SOLARISM 001

description:
Despertar' (Awakening) is a short film by Maria Cifuentes, a young Spanish director based in Paris, which explores the figurative depths of a woman's dream through the idea of transformation. A woman conceived as a contemporary Danae, dreaming of the golden rain and the elements of life.    https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lMTh3s0ElYU

Originally composed for the movie format, the film version comes here with two others versions by the composer ARNO E. MATHIEU, and a remix by the talented producer from Ukraine, VAKULA. 

True to the Balearic vibe of the film version, the Arno E. Mathieu « Mi Version » lifts the original mix to a long emotional journey,  driven by a strong rhythmic part and a hypnotic bass-line. The track grows until it reaches an epic breakdown and then returns to the cinematic roots of this composition before coming to a powerful ending.

Vakula’s remix is more like a dubby analog interpretation with some old synth and congas jams, adding new textures and bringing a more deep-house feeling to the project. Led by the personality of the man from Ukraine, this remix drives us slowly but surely to a real different vibe from the original track
title: Arno E Mathieu - Despetrar

description:
I was talking with Raoul K for few month about making African & European mixed music as a synthesis of our both culture before I heard "Le Tchadien" For the first time. When I finally discovered it, I immediately liked the feeling of the Singer and the guitar parts in the song. It was the perfect opportunity to make our conversation a reality. Raoul sent me the voice & guitar separated parts, then I started to do new music like drums, bass-lines and synthesizers and re-edit the whole song to make it works with my vision of the track.

After some sessions I finally sent my new version to Raoul K and we decided to release it !
title: RAOUL K & DOUNGOUS DEGOSPA - LE TCHADIEN - (ARNO E. MATHIEU VERSIONS)

description:
Vinyl sold out, digital available on Juno Download now: 
http://www.junodownload.com/products/olivier-boogie-ep/2718440-02/

"Dutch DJ and producer Olivier Boogie has been doing his thing in Amsterdam, largely without credit, for the best part of a decade. He's previously released both original productions and re-edits, with two contributions to a split Lumberjacks In Hell release back in 2012 standing out. Here he returns - at long last - with an edit EP of his own for Whiskey Disco. There's naturally much to admire, from the soaring strings, undulating bass and disco-funk hustle of "Got To Have Loving" and jaunty Rodriguez re-rub "Can't Get Away" being particularly potent. He also delivers a dash of head-nodding boogie ("You Know Who"), and turns a little-known funk jam into a shuffling house hustler ("Lost In The Crowd")."

description:
It's time to revisit one of the old releases of Stanislav Vdovin, performed in one of those small cafes. There are only 4 tracks left, compiled from different record takes. «Mandarins» is the only original here; the following «I Gather Sounds» is an excerpt from another live session. Stripped-down version of «Things Change» goes next, and the final number is «Freight» - previously unreleased ambient composition. 

Morning walk, hazy waters, wet soles; later — thick forest and urban jungle, and above all that — eternal inconstancy of heaven.

description: If you don't have a fear of open spaces sit beside on a cloud. Throw back your head and stare into space. We left autumn city somewhere below with all summer flashbacks. Sun spots on stone slabs, stems of grass through cracked asphalt — it's all past. Now the Sun is another star, and infinity rocks to sleep, sings a lullaby. Synthesizers (AudioRealism ABL Pro, Ensoniq TS-10, Arturia Jupiter-8V), samples, effects: Stanislav Vdovin Vocals (vocoder), field recordings (track 4): Alexander Ananyev Music and mastering by: Stanislav Vdovin Remix by: Alexander Ananyev (Sleepy Town Manufacture) Photo: Dmitry Daozor

description:
Although it is by far the dominant topic in most other forms of popular
music (and beyond that), love is not something that HipHop
artists talk about very frequently. There are many more rap songs
about recreational drug use, material wealth, not-quite-legal activities
or casual sex than there are about that other four letter word, L.O.V.E.

In comes „The Luv Bug“, a concept album entirely devoted to the big
topic: From the sparks of initially meeting an attractive woman (Familiar
Stranger) to planning the rest of your life together (Future Love),
from make-ups (Keep On Loving) to break-ups (Summer‘s Gone) and
from fantasizing about an ethereal beauty (Out Of Orbit) to deception
(Adesina), Chicago MCs Just Jay & Wisdm O.N.E. a.k.a. 1773 touch
on a wide variety of subjects.

The musical foundation is provided by the other end of this transatlantic
musical endeavour, producer Trishes from Vienna/Austria. He
manages to create quite different vibes - from spacey futuristic Beats
to almost classic Boom Bap sound and even farther back to 80s
drum computer patterns – while maintaining enough of a common
thread and feeling to keep the music cohesive. All together, this is a
pretty infectious record. Or, to quote from the intro: "The Luv Bug will
bite you if you don‘t watch out… Watch Out!“
tag_list: hiphop rap soul future boombap chicago chicagohiphop vienna
title: 1773 x Trishes - The Luv Bug

description:
When monsters kiss
Certainly, the music of Dnepr is gloomy, dim and in parts ominous. But it does not exhaust itself in
oppressive mud and bombastic lunacy. From the menacing swamp, sound figures rise from time to
time and find a moment of ethereal beauty, as if two monsters kiss each other before disappearing
again into murky ground fog and atonal madness.
With "Songs of No Return" Dnepr releases an album with a unique mix of guitar carpets, spherical
pads and dry drums. Impressive, oppressive and stunning at the same time.
title: Dnepr - Songs of No Return - Album Preview

WERNER HASLER | THE OUTER STRING - OUT TOO
OUT TOO is an installation, is a concert, is an exhibition

OUT TOO | the outer string | optickle | stettlerbros. 67

OUT TOO takes a look at a wildly romantic landscape of rocky edifices, forests and streams in the region of Krauchthal, through the lens of a semi-automatic eye. Origami-like images unfold to fill the space embedded in a sculptured sound-world, revealing a special piece of nature.

Sounds recorded on-site weave with the warm tones of actual and synthesised trumpets and celli.

OUT TOO takes the common contemporary idea of ‘experience before experience’ to a new level in a virtual-design reality and transforms a real piece of the world into a hyper-real event.*

*The real thing: 46°59’31.8“N 7°32’41.5“E
title: Werner Hasler | the outer string - OUT TOO - Album Preview

description:
*** Limited number of free copies available via www.moonstarr.bandcamp.com *** 

Moonstarr teams up with Montreal's Kelly Nunes on ‘Starlight’, a raw house cut with deep techno soul roots.  ‘Starlight’ evokes the fragmented memories of a past romance that flood the mind while driving through the city in the dead of night, steam rising from sewer grates. Drawing on inspiration from Abacus, Mark Flash, Recloose and Shawn Rudiman, the original keeps building with anticipation, while the energetic remix pays homage to early 90s club days in Toronto. 
 
Over the last two years, Moonstarr has released exclusive tracks on underground labels such as Pittsburgh’s Love What You Feel and Berlin’s Parages Music. A 12 inch EP is in the works for Adam Marshall’s New Kanada imprint, as well as the follow-up to Ill Harmonics Vol. 1 on PTR Music. ‘C-Minus Particles’ is still getting love four years on from the likes of George Fitzgerald, Art Department (BBC Radio 1 Essential Mix), Maceo Plex (featured his on Mixmag Dec. 2013 mix), and was recently licensed to a forthcoming Rainer Truby compilation on Compost Records.
 
Moonstarr continues to push innovative sounds on the long-running bi-weekly Future Classic Radio show on CKUT 90.3 FM in Montreal with co-host The One Tash. The show is available for stream on www.futureclassic.ca.
 
Fifteen years strong, Public Transit Recordings continues its mission to release cutting-edge Hip Hop, Future Soul and Electronic Music from Canadian and international artists. www.ptrmusic.com
 
Aroop Roy (Freestyle) “Nice late-night house vibes” 
DJ Hakobo (Fresco/SOM) “Light years of ill-ness”

Shuya Okino (Kyoto Jazz Massive) “Great tune!”
Eddy Ramich (Eddy Meets Yannah) “Sick track, love it”
Rainer Trueby (Root Down) “A real winner. I absolutely love this!”
title: Starlight EP Feat. Kelly Nunes - Out Now!

description: Kyoto Jazz Massive “Myster of Ages” Moonstarr Edits. Bridging Musical History from Canada to Panama to Japan ‘Mystery of Ages’ a lost classic composed by saxophone player and spiritual jazz funk legend Carlos Garnett in 1976. Reinterpreted by Japan’s dancefloor jazz purists Kyoto Jazz Massive. Remixed and reconfigured by Moonstarr.Now released on Public Transit Recordings, with proceeds going to Living Dreams, an organization supporting Japanese youth affected by the March 2011 earthquake. ‘Mystery of Ages’ was a personal challenge for Carlos back in 1976. A self-taught saxophonist, he pushed his boundaries in arrangement and scoring for a big band. That musical exploration became a journey posing big questions with a big sound, and captured the spirit of New York’s avant garde jazz funk community at that time. The song is a beautiful acknowledgement of our true naïveté about the universe, with Cheryl Alexander’s voice invoking questions about the meaning of human existence. Inspired by the original, Kyoto Jazz Massive (KJM) covered the song with a fresh take on ideas and arrangements, featuring Shota Hishiyama on Rhodes, Kenichi Ikeda (Root Soul) on bass, and the incredible Bembe Segue on vocals (who does justice to Cheryl’s original takes).Somewhere along the way, Moonstarr was given a sneak preview into KJM’s creative process via a bootleg of an acapella version of sorts.Persuaded by friend and fellow producer Yosaku, Moonstarr remixed the cover with his signature staccato breaks and chopped loop arrangements. With blessings from KJM and Carlos Garnett, PTR will release ‘Mystery of Ages – Moonstarr Remixes” on a limited 7inch in advance of KJM’s 2012 album release. Proceeds of the project will be going to Tohoku Kids Project (Living Dreams in collaboration with Smile Kids Japan), upholding Carlos Garnett’s ethos of passing on positive knowledge to younger generations. Living Dreams gives kids hope though alternative support such as supplying musical instruments to orphanages in the affected regions of Japan’s devastating earthquake of 2011. The only thing missing is Carlos’ sax. Stay tuned... Purchase the 7inch at these following links... Groove Distribution Juno UK Dusty Groove Digital... iTunes Juno Download Traxsource Beatport Public Transit Paypal
tag_list: "Kyoto Jazz Massive" "Bembe Segue" Japan Disco "Spiritual Jazz" "Carlos Garnett" "Broken beat" "Nu Jazz" Moonstarr Rhodes

The Archive - Unreleased and notable selections from the past.

Digging through dusty boxes of old cassette tapes, floppies and DATs, Moonstarr decided to compile some unreleased and classic joints from The Archive.This nostalgic look back reveals signature vinyl-only dancefloor jams praised by DJs and tastemakers the world over, as well as unreleased joints that are just now escaping Moonstarr's studio walls.

Previous vinyl-only joints include: 
Detriot:A deep house anthem originally released on Jazzanova’s Sonar Kollectiv in 2004. Misspelling intentional to con- nect back to tumultuous times of civil unrest in the city that birthed Techno. 
Greed Remix: Sweat-soaked samba dancefloor stormer originally released on Compost Records in 2003. 
Don't Sweat It: Batucada Tech sounds originally featured on Portugal’s Grooovement Records in 2005. 
The Recipe: A moody electro number originally released on Toronto’s Chair Records headed by Dan Lui in early 00's. 
Scarborough RT: Moonstarr’s contribution to the very first 12” released by PTR called Metropass showcasing the man’s musical obsessions, melting Hip Hop and Bossa Nova.

Unreleased joints hitting eardrums worldwide for the first time: 
Take It Back: Deep Techno rooted in the turn of the century and thick withY2K dreaming. 
Running: A moody tribute to the broken techno sounds of late 1990s in proto-broken beat era. 
Nasdaq: Quirky d’n’b tune created in response to the infamous dot com stock market crash in the late 1990s. 
Marz: As the rover landed on Mars countless space dreamers followed its adventures by eagerly examining all photos beamed back to Earth. 3-D glasses were adorned to examine this foreign landscape. Hence, a soundtrack was born.
title: The Archive (Moonstarr Retrospective)

description:
New 12inch release on PTR. Digital is available now on ptrmusic.com for $1.99. DJ Promos available as well get in touch.  

On this latest release, Moonstarr embarked on a series of late-night studio missions to explore the deep, moody regions of sound. Chopped breaks and dirty jazz loops are eschewed for synthesizers and drum machines to program the exploration into dark emotion and dissonance. Built upon the foundation created by steadfast pioneers like Mike Banks, Larry Heard, Shawn Rudiman, Purpose Maker and Drexcyia, and inspired by a conversation between Abacus and Marc Mac years earlier in which they discussed the need for vocals to permeate more techno music. Moonstarr continues the tradition and searches for the elusive 'C-Minus Particles' that disperse as quickly as they are created. On 'Monopoly', guest vocalist Tash sounds out a determined call for working-class justice overtop soaring synth lines, warm bass pulses and insistent rhythms. ILL Harmonics is part one in a series that will continue to travel the soundways in a complementary style to this release.

Feedback:

description: Ivano Tetelepta returns to duty on FOF after his well received 'True Colours' LP with a veritable potpourri of tracks in collaboration with various cohorts. First up Ivano's collaboration with Steve Siwalette twists and turns with a steppas' beat whilst melodic licks build the track up to it's anthemic break. 'Give Me Something So I Can Dance' w/Alex Jansen roughs things up with a low-slung dirty groove whist Ben Buiendijk injects an acidic flavour into his collaboration before Ivano & Bas Amro delve deeper with the sweetly melancholic tones of 'Manolia'
tag_list: "ivano tetelepta" "deep house" "fear of flying" "alex jansen" "bas amro" "ben buitendijk" "steven siwalette"
title: Ivano Tetelepta & Friends Vol 1

description: Nail provides the lead track for FOF's latest vinyl only excursion - originally produced in the same time period as the classic tracks on the 'Ode Rammel' reissue ep earlier in the year, 'Glazed' lay dormant on one of Nail's DATs for many years before being rediscovered and given it's first airing now on FOF. Chunky roughed up house beats are the order of the day here, a real peak time groove. New talent 'Harry McCanna', resident at London's infamous 'Undersound' nights, debuts with 'Act 1', a beautifully subtle bassline driven groove that rises above the pack with it's super warm pad lending the track a warm and fuzzy hypnotic edge. Romanian talent 'Zece' kicks off the flipside with the most contemporary offering; a breakbeat laden groove with a fx laden vocal snatch underpinned by that all important b-line whilst 'Sonodab' rounds things off with a beautifully deep and melodic slice of electro on 'Brown Study', the percussive elements giving rise to a hazy melodic pattern for those early hour excursions.
tag_list: Nail "Fear of flying" "harry mccanna" "vinyl only" sonodab zece romania house "tech house" "deep house"
title: Various Artists Volume 3

description: Roundtree could be the alias of a very well known (perhaps legendary) producer who might want to remain anonymous. We're not saying, or perhaps we just did, I'm not sure. Anyhow, two rather crisp housers on offer here, 'G-String Diva' with it's sharp as nails percussion and female spoken vocal which lends the track a nicely sleazy edge and 'No Need For the V' with it's prominent baseline driven grove.
title: Roundtree Presents - 12 Bit Joints

description: Roger Gerressen steps up to the plate for the next release on FOF's vinyl only imprint - 'Koshima' kicks things off with an elongated deep & submerged slice of dubbed out techno while the ante is most definitely upped on the flipsides 'Waka'; a shimmering groove with tripped out drums and blissful synth touches. 'Rendang Dub' plummets once more to the depths - reverbed kicks and claustrophobic bass lending the track a uniquely atmospheric edge.
title: Roger Gerressen - Koshima

description: Roger Gerressen switches to the main FOF label for his next release, 'Liberal' taking up the entirety of the A side with a killa' groove resplendent with knife edged percussion and tripped out synth stabs. Flipsides 'Mint' goes subaquatic with a serious slice of heads down bizinizz -  a male spoken vocal refrain repeats throughout to give a hypnotic edge. Lastly, Roger teams up with his buddy Smokin' G on 'Drunk Game', super rounded, housed up beats and an undulating synth / string line permeate the groove lending the ep a sense of levity.
tag_list: "Roger Gerressen" "Fear of Flying" "Dub Techno" House "Deep House"
title: Roger Gerressen - Liberal

description:
Fear of Flying delve into 2013 with a look back to the past with this solid 4 tracker of tracks from Nottingham's Nail. Originally released on the UK's revered DIY Discs imprint all the tracks on this ep have proven hard to get hold of over the preceding years with nary a copy available on Discogs for anything less than a King's Ransom. 

'Clear My Mind' was recently featured on Dyed Soundorom's DJ Mag covermount mix whilst 'Try' was included on Andrew Weatherall's early 'Essential' mixes and 'Til The Feelings Gone' was a standout on the recent Fabric compilation by Zip. With a pedigree like that its an easy choice to make, especially with the bonus cut 'Optimus' which proves to be the tougher of the 4 tracks giving a nice rounded edge to the ep.
title: Nail - Ode Rammel

description: These tracks were produced and recorded live on tapes somewhere between 1995 and 1997 in the basement of a squatted villa in Geneva, Switzerland, right at the foot of the giant Intercontinental Hotel that stands next to the United Nations building! When the house was evacuated I moved my studio, moved on to other projects and never released the tracks. They were played live from an Atari 1040ST computer with just a drum machine, an Akai S1000 sampler and a couple of synths. I recently rediscovered these tapes and decided to re-edit and remaster the tracks to give them a slightly more contemporary feel, while trying to retain the lo-fi, rebellious DIY spirit of those times. Reach for the lasers!
title: 1995-1997 The Lost Acid Tapes

description:
Late July will see Lower East’s founder Cozzy D release a two-track project on his very own imprint in the shape of ‘At The Rave’
Cozzy D has been at the helm of the Lower East imprint over the past six years A&Ring the imprint and welcoming the likes of Gerd, Larry Heard, MK, Kris Wadsworth and Alexis Raphael into its back catalogue. Amongst this Cozzy has branched out with his own material for reputable imprint such as ViVa Music, Material, Get Physical and of course his beloved home of Lower East.
Here though we see him return to the latter with two fresh cuts, the first of which ‘At The Rave’ takes the reins as the title-track and as the name would suggest embraces a nostalgic rave influence via bumpy breaks, heavy doses of sub bass, subtly blooming stab sequences and ethereal pad swells resulting in a contemporary twist on a classic format.
Closing is ‘Rub & Chugg’ which again is fittingly named and employs a slow-burning chuggy bass hook, and crunchy percussion alongside vacillating synth whirrs and hypnotic vocal licks.

Cozzy D’s ‘At The Rave’ is out on Lower East 29th July 2016.

description:
We’ve found the groove inside you since 2002, so why would we stop now? The bringthebeats underground exclusives are a mixed bag of sets compiled by our favourite artists from all over the globe.  Without a rigid release schedule, this collection allows us to share our love of house music with no strings attached. A set can be systematically compiled in studio or inspired by the punters on the dance floor.  Whenever a DJ is in the mood to share his or her talents with our crew, we’re here to deliver.  The lack of a concept is the perfect concept for the continuation of the bringthebeats community.  Our future is boundless… we invite you to stay TUNED!!

www.facebook.com/bringthebeats
www.twitter.com/bringthebeats

description:
We probably shouldn’t say we’ll never throw another party, because our track record isn’t so good when doing so.  However, if our 14yr anniversary party was our final jam, we couldn’t have ended our run in better fashion. We were on the Luke Fair and Brad Copeland tip from the very beginning and it would only be fitting if they were the ones who saw us out in the end.

Luke Fair’s set was a master class in groove, but we scored his INTIMATE & ON THE BOAT Summer Reunion set to share, so we thought it best we leave his anniversary set for those who were on the dance floor.  However, it’s been way too long since we hosted a live Brad Copeland mix in our archive, so that’s the memory we have to share here.

Part 1 is some of the most beautiful deep and ambient house we’ve heard, maybe ever at a bringthebeats event.  And when Brad really starts to warm the room in Part 2, we can virtually place ourselves back in front of the booth, lost in ecstasy.  After all these years, Brad hasn’t lost an iota of his mixing precision and his ear for gems is quite simply something he’s been blessed with. If this is the last live bringthebeats recording we ever share, Brad Copeland's given us the perfect mix to go out on.

Check out the pics here: www.facebook.com/pg/bringthebeats/photos/?tab=album&album_id=10154871771094559

Read the entire piece on bringthebeats:  www.bringthebeats.com/2016/12/16/btb-14yr-anniversary-brad-copeland-has-still-got-it

description:
Modeled after the Big DJ Small Club events of the legendary Gold Club series in the early 2000’s, INTIMATE & UNDERGROUND is our event promotion’s signature party at TOiKA in Toronto, Canada. After three test runs in the venue, we launched the series on our sixth anniversary in October 2008.

We joined forces with the Rogers Wireless Box Office to help beta test their new mobile ticketing technology and in the process provided the first five INTIMATE & UNDERGROUND‘s for FREE!! The first 11 I&U’s were bringthebeats solo missions, but from v12 to v27 they were co-promoted alongside the Groove Garden Recordings crew. Also born from the series and the Groove Garden partnership was INTIMATE & ON THE BOAT, which has featured three killer groove cruises. Both series were put to rest in August 2014.

In the summer of 2015 we retuned for an INTIMATE & UNDERGROUND reunion at TOiKA and an INTIMATE & ON THE BOAT reunion aboard the majestic Tall Ship Kajama. It’s not easy for us to stay away from the dance floor, either at TOiKA or on the Kajama, so expect more reunion jams in the unforeseeable future.

For now, here are adventures we’ve been able to capture for the world’s aural pleasure. We hope you love them as much as we continue to.

description:
Craig Anderson has been a staple in the Toronto club scene from the very beginning.  From Industry to System Soundbar, Element, Boa-Redux and all the coolest parties in between, if the music’s great, you know Craig’s somewhere in the room.  And when the music’s really great, there’s a good chance he’s controlling things in the booth.  

Craig’s first bringthebeats gig was in 2011 and he’s spun many incredible sets for us at TOiKA and on our cruises ever since.  Setting the stage for the likes of Luke Fair, Ian Pooley, Ricky Ryan, Jody Wisternoff and Omid 16B, Craig’s silky smooth and sexy style perfectly sets the bringthebeats vibe.  And his peak time sets at Parlour, inside the CTRL ROOM and even for Electric Circus back in the day, have had dance floors locked in a serious groove.  

bringthebeats wouldn’t have come nearly as far as we have it if weren’t for the support and tunes of Craig Anderson. As you’ll hear in this playlist, Craig puts all of his heart and soul into each promo mix and the results are timeless. He’s one of a kind in the club industry.  We’re so fortunate to have Craig Anderson in the bringthebeats crew. 

SOUNDCLOUD: @cranderson
www.facebook.com/craig.anderson.5011516

description:
In the summer of 2007 four prominent club promotions joined forces to organize a weekly event that wasn’t just about booking big names over and over and over again. EXPOSED was about bringing underground music back to the forefront.  We were out to create a house.music.re-evolution.

For our crew it had been since the early days of Breathe at System Soundbar. For the others it was in the beginning with Industry or at the incredible 270 Spadina space, Sonic / Boa-Redux. Regardless of wherever or whenever, for all of us, it had been way too long since a Toronto club night was truly dedicated to the underground, so we did something about it

EXPOSED hosted four distinct events each month…

bringthebeats championed the funky progressive house sound with former Stereo in Montreal, Atomic in Ottawa and System Soundbar resident Brad Copeland as the top jock for all bringthebeats bookings.  We also brought on Toronto favourite @djjeffbutton for one of his first residencies. 

Energie Entertainment enlisted DJs Addy & Neno for a week of serious party tunes. The cornerstone of EXPOSED, LIV Lifestyle Marketing supported the tribal and classic house sounds with @djaddy returning as resident for their nights.  And NocturnalMagazine.net & Till The AM featured an array of soulful vocal house to dirty tech and electro with @djandyreid and @simon-jain opening their nights. 

We took over Fridays at The Mod Club Theatre, home to the world famous Brit Pop Saturdays, as well as a rocking live-to-air on Thursdays. We hosted guest lists, promoted the parties and documented each night with reviews and pics on the EXPOSED website.  We’ve recreated some of the original posts in the mix descriptions and included the bringthebeats promo CDs, live sets and EXPOSED-inspired sets in the playlist below.  

For the better part of a year our Friday nights were EXPOSED.  We met some of our best friends and supporters on The Mod Club dance floor and the series paved the way for the INTIMATE & UNDERGROUND era that followed.  We’ll never forget our nights with @holosoundnyc, Luke Morrison, @rickyryan, @neil-quigley (twice), @naveen-g, @eliwilkie, @jodywisternoff and @terry-lee-brown-junior. And thanks to the ever-lasting memories in this music, we’ll never have to.

description:
Get this on Beatport here: http://bit.ly/rWzcap


Tronicsole continues it recent run of form with this release showcasing the Brighton based new talent of Peter O. Comes packaged with a cracking Kris Wadsworth remix. 

Here is everything you need to know about Peter O: 

"I first got in to House Music in the late 1980's and I remember thinking to myself that I had found "My Music!" I also remember running home from school to listen to "Centreforce FM"! I started DJing in the early 1990's and have played on the London circuit since then. I always new that I wanted to produce my own beats but it wasn't until about 7 years ago that I decided to study Music Technology and Sound Recording. Since then I have had a few tracks out and I continue to write new music every day!" 

When we received his demos at Tronicsole, the music spoke for itself.

title: Ecoutes au vert/Music for Indoors mix series
Aphex Twin - Best of Covers, Remixes & Homages

description:
Richard D James output & career are just incredible, there is so much good stuff... Piano, Ambient, IDM, Rave, Techno & more...! Spanning over a period of 30+ years. 

His music is not only great technically, wonderfully lightheaded, pop, trippy or viscerally intense at times, but also emotionally deep. It is the work of a composer in a modern contemporary way.

I was going through some of his music on SC and decided to make myself an Anthology Playlist grouping tracks from several accounts, incl. @user18081971 where he dumped a lot of great music back in 2015 and continues sporadically to do so. Many of which you can also download for free! 

This is a pretty large selection of his music, but still slightly suggestive to my tastes, I included most of what I've found here on Soundcloud though. 

It's an ongoing effort too, if you think I missed this or that track, live set, dj recording or interview, or upload something that isn't on SC yet, drop me a message with the link(s) for consideration to be added, this Playlist is for everyone to enjoy.

I started to do this for myself but soon thought I will share it to all of you music lovers, fans and people knowing only a bit of his music, but most importantly I wonder/imagine there are teenagers and young people that barely know his music, especially the very early stuff. Seeing how the 80's, 90's and 00's go through revivals and are constantly reprocessed, I realized it's important to expose Aphex Twin's work with such an Anthology Playlist on an important DJ, Producers, Listeners Platform such as Soundcloud, still a great place where there are lots you can't find on Spotify or other streaming places.

Thanks so much for the wonderful music Richard... <3 
.
.
Rich holds contact with fans on @user18081971 in the threads of some of the tracks. There are also advice and FX for sampling and making music. :)

On one thread, he told people to share interesting youtube links and posted his: 

RDJ links: www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLX…0d35H2XTHSafEOcUL

Pubilc linx: www.youtube.com/watch?v=PODlgcLsh…m8hGfl42&index=88

Here below is the complete list of the 200-plus Aphex Twin demos uploaded on Soundcloud in 2015 before his user account was then deleted (nowadays end of 2020, the account features 46 tracks), which came after with a multipage Google Doc including James’s own release notes and further minute details about the recordings. https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/11ouNaaVrNp60Ib34Kp0TO1n1XSc7-9DvfiZ9ZiTiD2c/htmlview#

description:
Art is Trouble is my 4th album, and my deep wish that imagination and arts can lead the world to a better state. 

Every change requires from us to overcome some trouble, easiness and sometimes even pain. By this condition our lives can go forward in a process of becoming what we are.

To those who have, are being or will have to leave their place of birth for another in order to have a better life.

To those who try to change their habits for a better place for their children.

To those who struggle to have their voices heard through their opinion or their art, in countries where silence reigns.


This album wouldn’t be possible without my family, my friends and my listeners. Infinite thanks Dears.

Thanks to Ripperton and Azenoire for their kind participation, to Delphine Sandoz, Tammam Azzam, Eleni Ntouva, Azenoire for the artworks, to Anna for the lyrics corrections.
title: Art is Trouble

description:
Intimacy is my first album, built up over the last two years of music production. I tried to transcribe the people, moods, ideas that shared my creative process and my life everyday.

This album is always a relation of one to one ; like a couple, a spectator, an intervenor. It often mentions reflection, image and projection. As an analysis of the social and relational substance that makes any possible interpretation.

Have a nice listening
Van Hai
title: Intimacy, Album 2010

description:
Preconscious
the mental function in which thoughts, ideas, emotions, or memories not in immediate awareness can be brought into the consciousness, usually through associations, without encountering any intrapsychic resistance or repression.

-

Dear friends and listeners,
a few words about what this album 'preconscious' and its genesis.
His first title i chose for her perfect ability to define this place in mind which arise the emotions, then the senses images, stored in memory, accessible when the process of awareness.
At the base of the project, i chose the name of my son who was still 'in the pipeline', it is this impulse that i started to work: how to welcome and get ready myself at his coming. Then i felt the need to broaden the spectrum, about the conditions necessary for this coming, approaching love, trust, endurance. Desiring to do a 'fiction' i kept the title ‘arya’ only realistic trace of this birth. So i talk about these choices, those who gather and those who separate, the various crucial stages of a relationship, the desire to remain upright, prepare and keep his way, and that which is done to my family.
From my current location as well as the cultural and generational clash that every day i measure the size, i wanted to attempt a dialogue. it certainly there's much moral in this project and i fully assume. I have the ambition to share this aspect of my life with the generations that follow, the photographic and visual choices and some of the texts are illustration of it. And to go back to the preconscious, this need has been paired with this sudden realization.
Some may find this album less researched, less dense and much less dancing than before. As some of you know, i no longer recognize myself in this square of green that is music for clubbing. This format, nor its rationale doesn’t represent me at the moment. With this album, i take off, leaving the scene that brought me so she forced me. I do not know my next destination, but hope to see you there and hopes that you will find refuge in this latest opus as a welcoming and warm.

Regards 
Van Hai
title: Preconscious - Album

description:
Please Click the Buy link in the player to access to the donation form. Thanks in advance!

Français

Introduction / charte

« Exile » est un projet musical, artistique et intellectuel ouvert dans le temps et l’espace, mis en œuvre pour faire face à la montée de la xénophobie et de l’intolérance en Europe et plus généralement dans les pays dits « développés ».

« Exile » n’est le fruit d’aucune idée politique de quelque aile que ce soit et n’acceptera aucune récupération. « Exile » est le fait de personnes ayant connu l’émigration pour des raisons économiques, humanitaires ou politiques. Ce projet est avant tout leur manière de partager leur expérience, leurs sentiments sur ce sujet.

En dehors de toute idéologie et religion, les œuvres présentées sont autant de messages personnels - qu’ils soient adressés à ceux qui les soutiennent, ou a ceux qui les condamnent - lancés contre le mur de l’indifférence.

Nous, producteurs et artistes exilés, prenons ainsi la liberté de parler en notre nom et de ne plus accepter que les autres le fassent à notre place pour se rendre populaires, attirer leur électorat ou vendre leurs idées.

Nous ne demandons rien d’autre en échange de l’utilisation des œuvres de ce projet que le respect de ceux qui les ont produites, en les mentionnant. Nous invitons également ceux qui le souhaitent à faire un don en faveur de la Croix-Rouge, aujourd’hui pour les exilés d’Afrique du nord et demain pour d’autres qui seront forcés de partir de chez eux, mais qui ne le savent pas encore.

Nous espérons que ce projet suscitera l’intérêt ainsi que le désir de parole chez certains jusque là silencieux ou orientés vers d’autres sujets.

Tous les détails seront accessibles prochainement depuis le site web : www.mescene.com/exile/

Conditions de participation au projet

Sera accueilli à bras ouverts celui qui a quelque chose à partager sur ce sujet, par le média de son choix mais dans le respect des lignes précédentes. Les opinions ne nous intéressent pas, nous voulons de vraies expériences.

musicien et producteur, plasticien, co-manager du label Mescene records et membre du collectif Corporari

écrivain, éditée chez Luce Wilquin

English

Introduction / charter

"Exile" is a musical, artistic and intellectual project open in time and space, initiated in response to the rise of xenophobia and intolerance in Europe and more generally in so-called "developed" countries.

"Exile" is not the result of any political idea whatsoever, and will not accept any misappropriation. "Exile" is a creation of people who have experienced emigration for economic, humanitarian or political reasons. This project is a way to share their experiences, their feelings on this subject.

Regardless of ideology and religion, the works presented are personal messages. They are addressed to those who support, or those who condemn them - thrown against the wall of indifference.

We, producers and artists in exile, thus take the liberty to speak on our own behalf and stop accepting others to do it in order to get popular, obtain votations or sell their ideas.

We ask for nothing else in exchange for the use of these works but to respect their authors by mentioning them. We also invite those who wish to make a donation to the Red Cross to exiled persons from North Africa and for others who will be forced to leave their homes in the future.

We hope this project will make want to speak up some of those who have remained silent or were turned to other subjects.

All details will soon be available on the website:
www.mescene.com/exile/

Conditions for participation in the project

We welcome anyone who has something to share on this subject in the media of their choice, but in respect of the above-mentioned. We are not interested in opinions, we want real experiences.

List of Participants (to 19th of march 2011)

Van Hai (Vietnam-Switzerland-Lao PDR)
musician and producer, plastician, co-manager of the label Mescene records and member of Corporari collective

David Durango (Spain-Switzerland)
musician and producer, co-manager of the label Mescene records

Dawad (Lao PDR-France)
musician and producer, co-manager of the label IRM records

Masaya (Chili-Switzerland)
musician and producer, manager of the label Mina Records

Laure Mi Hyun Croset (Korea-Switzerland)
writer, edited by Luce Wilquin

Alvaro Del Canto (Chili-Switzerland)
plastician and graphic designer, member of Corporari collective
            
Anna Maria Phayouphorn (Germany-Switzerland)
art historian, editorial collaborator, translator and archivist

Deutsch

Einführung/Charta

“Exile” ist ein künstlerisch-musikalisches Projekt, das räumlich und zeitlich unbegrenzt ist. Es wurde angesichts der zunehmenden Xenophobie und Intoleranz in Europa und den so genannten entwickelten Ländern ins Leben gerufen.

“Exile” entspringt keiner politischen Intention und soll nicht zu politischen Zwecken missbraucht werden.

“Exile” wird von Menschen geschaffen, die Emigration erlebt haben, sei es aus wirtschaftlichen, humanitären oder politischen Gründen. Dieses Projekt soll ihnen ermöglichen, sich auf ihre Art und Weise zu diesem Thema zu äußern.

Die vorgestellten Arbeiten sind persönliche Botschaften ohne religiöse oder ideologische Absichten. Sie richten sich an diejenigen, die ihre Autoren unterstützen oder kritisieren – ein Aufschrei gegen die Gleichgültigkeit.

Zu oft wird der Migrationsdiskurs missbraucht - wir nehmen uns die Freiheit, durch unsere Werke als Exilanten für uns selbst zu sprechen.

Die Werke sind frei zugänglich und verwendbar. Als einzige Gegenleistung bitten wir darum, dabei die Namen ihrer Autoren zu nennen. Außerdem rufen wir dazu auf, über das Rote Kreuz an heutige oder zukünftige Flüchtlinge zu spenden.

Wir hoffen, dass dieses Projekt einige betroffene dazu animiert ihr Schweigen zu brechen, oder sich mit diesem Thema zu beschäftigen.

Für Einzelheiten steht bald folgende Website zur Verfügung: www.mescene.com/exile

Bedingungen für die Beteiligung am Projekt:

Wir begrüßen jeden, der sich mit einem Beitrag im Medium seiner Wahl am Projekt beteiligen möchte, unter den oben genannten Voraussetzungen. Wir brauchen keine Meinungen, wir suchen Menschen, die selbst Exil erfahren haben.

description:
Morris Audio 112: Joint4Nine - the house definition ep
out digitally mid October.

Morris Audio add some south american house flavour to their artist roaster! Please welcome Joint4Nine from Bogota/Colombia for his definition of house music. Joint4Nine (or Ivan Lozano to his parents) is a busy man when it comes to music. He’s a DJ, producer and label owner – yes, he runs Nomada Records with one of the hotshots of the year, Felipe Gordon. The house definition EP is proper old school house with all you love – beats, basslines, samples, pianos, vocals and much more! We’ll house you!
title: Morris Audio 112: Joint4Nine - the house definition ep

description:
Morris Audio 111: Tree Threes - lies & space ep
out mid august.

Irish born and London based Tree Threes is back on Morris Audio with his second ep of proper house music! “Fabulous lies” spreads much classic house vibes with pianos and vocals yet keeping a deep feel. “Spacious retreat” is slightly darker and shines with some dope drums. Last but not least “What’s up with ye”, a punchy slightly toolish tunes for all you DJs out there. Well done TT!
title: Morris Audio 111: Tree Threes - lies and space ep

description:
Morris Audio 110: Decent Rides - uncertain times EP
out late May.

Morris Audio’s hunt for hot talents brings you Decent Rides, a project from the Bavarian natives Sebastian and Jesko. Being openmindend DJs for many years, Decent Rides intend to develop a sound that reflect their eclectic taste, incorporating hip-hop, jazz, disco and of course house. The „uncertain times“ EP presents perfectly their style with some ruff and rugged yet deep tunes! Check out their releases on Quintessentials, Nervous NYC, the Basement Discos, See Saw or Sundries too. Niceness
title: Morris Audio 110: Decent Rides - uncertain times EP

description:
Morris Audio 109: Formasoul - get into the groove (incl. Chocky and Wearing Shoes remixes)
Digitally out early April.

Morris Audio welcomes another new exciting member to the family: Formasoul from Berlin! His “Get into the groove” is a classic deep and dubby House tune for more relaxed occasions. On remix duty is Chocky, no stranger to the scene with several releases on labels like Big Bait or Steve Bug’s Dessous Recordings. His remix keeps the deep and dubby vibe, but adds more club flavour to make this a perfect early or late hours tune. Last but not least is Wearing Shoes (aka Alfonso Bottone), who provides his signature string laden House style. All killers no fillers!
tag_list: "Morris Audio" Formasoul "Get into the groove" Chocky "Wearing Shoes"
title: Morris Audio 109: formasoul - get into the groove

description:
Morris Audio 108: Tree Threes - going deeper
Digitally out mid February.

Morris Audio is always on the hunt for new talents, and it looks that irish lad Tree Threes is one of them! “Going deeper” is his debut release on Morris Audio (TT also releases on Nervous NY) and shows what Tree Threes loves: proper house music! “The warehouse” is an ode to 80’s acid house music and appreciation for the Warehouse Club in Chicago. “Going Deeper” is a garage influenced dark deep house tune and “Feelin’ it” is that slow burner with a deep minimal feel. Welcome to the family, Tree Threes!

description:
Number 6 of Estroe's Rosedale Records brings you a release by Estroe herself.
The titles of the tracks expresses Estroe's love for nature. Myosotis Arvensis (Field Forget Me Not) and Tanacetum Parthenium (Feverfew) are two of her favourite flowers which bloom in June, the month of the release date.

Two highly regarded friends and fellow producers were invited for the remix honours, Berlin based Glitterbug and (music) BFF Nadia Struiwigh.

Estroe's original mix of Myosotis Arvensis starts with a simple but intriguing bassline and slowly builds amidst delicate, melodic patterns and lush, orchestral strings as if the flowers themselves are opening one by one. Her natural sense of groove prevails in the bassline throughout this meadow of fresh, early summer sound.

Tanacetum Parthenium (original) has an edgier feel to it. Again it is groove driven by a distinctive bassline but is awash with a tense, almost organic background and with darker percussive shots. Brooding orchestral swells bring to the track a sense of salient anxiety.

Glitterbug's Desperate Times remix of Myosotis Arvensis has an orchestral and cinematic quality. Deep sustained bass notes and a fluid and metallic rhythm drive this track along elegantly. The smooth solemn strings and glistening pads wrap this track in a cloak of sonic grace.

His other remix on the ep, Glitterbug's That Very Moment remix is a sublime piece of aural architecture. Ambient, emotional and with a heartbeat bass drum, it encapsulates the very moment one is struck by the tranquillity of seeing something beautiful. The strings in this track ebb and flow like serene breaths of cool air whilst the soft piano shimmers like early morning dew.

Always one to explore the deeper side of a track, like a botanist in a lab, Nadia Struiwigh dissects the original Tanacetum Parthenium and creates a remix which exemplifies her style. She creates a dark and pulsating mix of throbbing bass drums, cavern like reverbs and ominous, overdriven grooves that build the track perfectly.
title: ROSE008 Estroe Spring Flowers EP

description:
In January of 2006, I launched my very first series of mixes, which I called "liftmuziek", focused on IDM, modern classical, and ambient electronica. The sixteen volumes eventually became a podcast, and then, somewhere along the way, Headphone Commute was born. The rest, as they say, is history. 

I nearly forgot about these mixes, as the remnants of poorly encoded files slowly disappeared from the internet archives. That is... until now... Nearly by accident, I was able to locate all of the 16 Volumes in their original lossless resolution on one of my dusty hard drives!!! 

These are now being released, one at a time, for all your guilty pleasures, to celebrate the sounds of electronica from the good ol' days :)

description: Terrace returns to EevoNext with this 3 track EP. Out of time resembles his continuous struggle to match the daily time frames and deadlines. if only FTL travel would be possible, this would make a huge difference! Unfortunately he finds himself Framed as resembled by the second track. Mekanika is a more freestyle approach caused by having a spare moment in the studio.
title: Time Frames EP

description: A complete CD album offering 10 songs made by Terrace over the last 7 years. As night falls, the road before you unfolds. Slowly, all the bustle dissipates. Tarmac becomes visible, the horizon changes colour: evening comes. Time to consider your journey, time for music. This is where this album originates and this is where it is heading. Thought leads to music and music leads to thought. Inspiration, action and reaction. The passing of time is the context. Where are you coming from and where are you going to? May these be interesting times.
title: Interesting Times

description: There can't be many people who have made more excellent releases than Stefan Robbers and this album has some perfectly crafted tracks. From the layered complex drum patterns of Inspiria, to the dreamy armchair journey of Into Deep Space and to the driving, almost clubby The Scream, this album has it all for the discerning listener. A little stab at the rave scene in The Scream is provided by the lyric "One day you will be half-dead begging for a decent meal - if only you had listened instead of dancing like an imbecil (sic)". Very pointed Stefan - but some of us always listened to your music! If you like well-made tech-house, make sure you have this.
title: Konnekt

description: The first album by Terrace Aka Stefan Robbers, recorded at Shanta Studio in Eindhoven in 1991. It is compilation tracks gathered over a 2 year period, and some new fresh ideas from that era. It was released as the first techno cd album on Djax-up-beats records. It also was released on vinyl as a double lp with a gatefold sleeve.
title: Round Up

description: Released during the 90's around the same time when classic quality Idm-techno/ambient albums: Black Dog 'Bytes', Aphex Twin 'Selected Ambient Works 85-92', B12 'Electro Soma', Speedy J 'Ginger', Reload 'A collection of short stories'..etc; were released - 'Occurrence' sadly got lost amongst the onslaught of quality electronic albums from the 90's! A excellent fusion of European/Detroit influenced 90's techno with drum-melodic characteristics of Idm, along with ambient flourishes and some cool intelligent use of techno-breakbeat,delivering a creative post-modern si-fi listen with a solid electronic/techno foundation that keeps this album interesting throughout without failure. This is a sort of album that would not be out of place from Warp's own classi Artifical Intelligence series - you can certainly relate to the AI feel and sound onthis album. Today (2018+) `Occcurance’ remains a great album with music that will manage to stimulate the mind, the soul & the body while complementing everything good about techno without depending on repetition or harshness in its sound.. This is quality techno in every sense that should be placed along with classic known techno albums that were ahead of there time but still remain a joy to listen today.
title: Occurences

description: 4 unreleased pearls from from the vault of this legendary artist!Recording as Terrace, Florence, and under his own name, Robbers has been responsible for some of the most memorable moments in experimental dance music in the last few years, from the first release on the now-commanding D-Jax label (Terrace's 1990 EP 916 Beuna Avenue) to recent Terrace and Florence full-lengths released on his own Eevo Lute imprint.

description:
Release page (with free DL): http://astorbell.com/?release=ephedra

Compared to the more playful debut, Socket Science slows things down on the follow up Ephedra. Three dark, distorted and long jams that focus on the lower frequencies yet remain true to the core idea, being Robot Music with Soul.

It's easy to envision lined up drones doing their monotonic labour in dirty factories. However, these pieces of music also carry the reverberation of their children playing on the school yard across the street, as well as the moans and squeaks of the community elders in need of an oil tin refreshment. Everyone's invited, everyone plays a part.

And not to forget; all these influences and emotions are packed upon a quite steady and bouncy beat. Do your club a favor and spin it.
title: Ephedra (ASTOR013)

Reviews:
5 Mag CHICAGO: "Deep Core: A month with Malcolm Moore's Long Awaited Album" https://5mag.net/tracks/new-releases/malcolm-moore-deep-core/
Juno: 'Minneapolis deep house veteran Malcolm Moore returns to his own label Altered Moods with another blissful excursion into the farthest realms of smoked-out expression. It takes but a moment to sink into "Everydaelife" and place this sound - the kind of pattering rhythm sections and powerfully melancholic chords that you'd expect from the likes of Dubbyman, Anton Zap or Ron Trent. Moore has his own take on things though, bringing a blown out jack to the table on "Own The Nite (90s House Rescrub)"and creating a moving, downtempo funk on "Lunchtime Gaze". The more forthright grooves are impeccable too though - "Rodalies R1" hits every sweet spot a deep house lover could wish for.'

description:
11th Hour Recordings is back with ‘Endless Days’, our most dancefloor excursion so far - 4 slamming new techno and electro cuts, starting with the outrageously tough beat and grinding basslines of ‘Kick It’, followed by a stunning high-tech-funk remake by Motech main man and UR assault squad member DJ 3000; who takes the heavy bass of the original and layers on new jazzed out synth hooks and stripped down percussion.
On the flip, ‘Cold Restraint’ is a straight out dancefloor bomb - tough driving percussion threaded with a distorted bleep hook and searing strings, all pushed forward by one of the nastiest basslines around; whilst ‘Down and Out in EC2′ provides a deep, driving and endlessly shiftingelectro workout.

This release is already getting rave reviews from press and public worldwide, with DJ magazine making it ‘Electro single of the month’ Feb 09 and Update naming it ‘Essential single of the month’, as well as featuring in M8, Fact, Mixmag and many others. It is getting strong DJ support from Laurent Garnier,UR, Fabrice Lig, Mark Broom and many more…

The Middlesbrough Art Weekender is a contemporary arts festival, celebrating and promoting international and local artists in the heart of the Tees Valley. With ‘Connectivity’ as this years theme, the festival promotes Middlesbrough Town Centre as a cultural and artistic hotspot.

Middlesbrough Art Weekender & Singing Tees Bridges generously supported by: Arts Council England, Tees Valley Combined Authority, MIMA [Middlesbrough Institute of Modern Art], River Tees Rediscovered, Middlesbrough Council, Creative Darlington, Heritage Lottery Fund & Middlesbrough Holiday Inn. igloomag.com/reviews/dr-nojoke-muaco-clickno

Videoclip Muaco by VJ Lilitxt
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HvNYF_Hu5HU


In 2021 CLIKNO celebrates its 5th anniversary and presents with its 10th release a very special acoustic techno EP from Dr.Nojoke entitled “Muaco.

This EP is a child of the Corona crisis. Muaco stands for Music against Corona and deals with the clubless time we are all experiencing.

When Dr.Nojoke picked up his Höfner acoustic guitar during the lockdown in spring he was looking for new inspirations. The recordings led to three brilliant poly-rhythmical tracks for a special trip far off the beaten path.
Dr.Nojoke suggests his EP as much as a way for home-clubbing as well as a listening experience.

We don´t even know, if it is techno or what, but as mostly all parts were created with acoustic guitar you may file it under acoustic techno or guitar techno.
We think it is just great groovy music - pulsating, hypnotic, danceable, kraut-ish, freaky - that should be played everywhere.
tag_list: "Minimal Techno" clikno Acoustic "acoustic guitar" electronica "electronic music" "deep techno" hypnotic "kraut techno" "organic techno"
title: Dr.Nojoke - Muaco [CLIKNO D05]

description:
Part II
https://microrama.bandcamp.com/album/anomali-drones-tones-for-the-free-ii

Part I
microrama.bandcamp.com/album/anomali-drones-tones-for-the-free

All music was created with a Farfisa Compact organ, effects and a mixing desk. No overdubs, no mastering, just as rough as recorded!

Why Drones & Tones For the Free?
In these times of growing fears I'd like to give in something to think and meditate on. Drones & Tones For The Free can be understood as an abstract title, but I really mean it literally: it's about freedom!
Free are those, who free their hearts and souls from fear, hate, anger, greed, jealousy ... We have to free us from fascism, racism, sexism ... and any kind of oppressive and manipulative act, which is build on inequality and on the system of fear, that creates even more fear, through which people control others.
We cannot accept that.
It is obviously just so wrong.

I think we can be free only, when we fight our fears, when we manage to become independent from the sources of fear. Fear makes us blind.
We must free our hearts and minds to act and think without preoccupations and prejudices, to be open, to feel responsible, feel empathy and act socially again.
It really starts with everyone.

Drones & Tones For The Free is an invitation and a call to start with it right now!
title: Anomali - Drones & Tones For The Free II

description:
https://clikno.bandcamp.com/album/ai-mat-ed-02


AI.
The second output in the MAT editions series on CLIKNO is a bass-heavy affair over four sides by Dr.Nojoke. Separated into the EPs “Anonymity” and “Intimacy” it is due to be released on August 7th, 2020.
The digital world and social media in particular change our perception and behavior; our values and morals undergo a transformation and shift. How much are we still anonymous? How much are we still intimate (with us/with others)? What does anonymity and intimacy mean to us today?

MUSIC.
Dr.Nojoke shows on AI his deeper, darker, bassier and trippier side.
A. Petar Plet Plete is based on a Bulgarian tongue twister. The chant hypnotizes with its layers and endless repetitions over a straight Maurizio-esque groove with melodic percussion in odd time signature. Nivin grooves elegantly with typical Dr.Nojoke clicks and sophisticated loops of a mysterious female voice, whose melody reminds slightly to Kraftwerk’s Man-machine era.
I. EOW and Nuknot are both intimate orgies of thick textures of reverberations and reflections as if space is folding in itself and time is on hold. EOW seduces with a heavy kick-drum groove and a triplet bassline underneath crawling through unconscious memories. Woe! Nuknot is carried by eternal atmospheres, a low end bassline and a repetitious glassy clang, that can drive a crowd into madness - inspired by Moritz von Oswald and Deadbeat. Nuknot ends in an ambient lock groove

ART.
CLIKNO curates artworks from living artists. For MAT ed.02 we are proud to present digital artist Lucas Gutierrez and his work “Your Mesh.sgl”, originally part of the exhibition ▬ Knowledge Of ▬ at Aperto Raum Berlin, 2017. An exhibition and dialogue exploring the term “knowledge” and the manner in which self-studies are structured within contemporary artistic approach.

TEXT.
MAT02 comes with writings to anonymity and intimacy from the Danish philosopher, actress and choreographer Marianne Kjaer Klausen.
