description:
Up next on Upon You Rec. is Hartford, Connecticut-based producer Eddie Merced, a name that’s been making waves since his debut - “From Within” - came out in 2016, earning himself instant praise from seminal figures like Laurent Garnier. Stepping up with a trio of his signature oneiric, mind-expanding wares, Eddie takes us on an odyssey-like voyage into the deeper end of techno’s atmospheric spectrum, making the rounds from alien-engineered architectonics towards velveteen, near-lounge-y abstraction.

The journey begins with “Towards A Dream” - a self-revealing roller beaming us up to far-flung Saturnian lands as it unfolds a slo-hatching meshwork of sun-washed pads, raucous bass work and boggy 303 talk. Rising the pressure a notch further, “High Virgo” is a laser-guided weapon aimed at subjugating dance-floors through steadfast onslaughts of delayed drums, gut-churning kicks and Eddie's typical hi-intensity synth hoodoo from outer-space. Last but not least, UY co-founder Marco Resmann adds his havoc-wreaking, dynamic spin to “Towards A Dream”, turning the dreamy original into a full-fledged club destroyer, primed for ruff n'tuff peak time action. Equally at ease in an open-air setting or busting kneecaps in the darkness of a jam-packed basement.
tag_list: "Eddie Merced" "Towards A Dream" "Marco Resmann" Remix EP Single "Upon You Records" "Deep House" Techno "Melodic House" "Melodic Techno"
title: Eddie Merced - Towards A Dream

description: It's time to step out of the dense fog of days past, tempted by the deeply reverberating siren's call of 'Visions of Clarity', Collate's maiden voyage EP on Upon You. While 'Glossolalia's thumping, heads-down beat locks you into an airtight vacuum from the go, Daniela Rhodes' beguiling vocal slithers soon guide us into a shimmering landscape of dubbed-out synths and craftly placed effects. These are only brought to the fore by label-head Marco Resmann on his 'Re-Edit One'. Here, a chunky metallic groove unspools into an echo-chamber of infinite depth. In contrast, Resmann's 'Re-Edit Two' ups the ante by adding a neon-synth overload to the mix, making for an equally immersive result. On 'Backpfeifengesicht' Collate then strips things down for the after-hour, letting disoriented bleeps tap-dance over a hugely satisfying minimalist framework, reminding us of the early 90s sound-axis between Berlin and the north of England. Lastly, Collate activates the bunker vibes by way of 'Awumbuk', concluding a powerful EP with a viciously moreish bomb. This one's for those bleary-eyed moments we've come to miss so much. Let's enjoy them while we can.
tag_list: "Upon You Records" Collate "Daniela Rhodes" "Marco Resmann" "Deep House" "Tech House" Techno Release Remix Edit
title: Collate - Visions Of Clarity

description:
And they are back once again. Of course we are talking about Eins Tiefer, the famed duo comprised of Vincent Probst and Nico Bulla, who are set and well ready to unleash their latest musical outing via Upon.You Records these days which is their four track single called „Retrograde“.

Starting their musical journey with „Sliced“ the dynamic duo comes in on a surprisingly deep and tender tip, fusing a slow, yet still TechHouse-leaning foundation with super soft, carefully arranged pad structures and multiple layers of African chants – a combination for late night sets in small, intimate club settings and defo one that might cause a bit of an Ambient House revival to come, transferring this classic term into a new and contemporary context.

Subsequently Eins Tiefer are bringing forth „Flurry“ which defo feels more at home on the dark side with its brooding, analogue basslines and eerie crackles atop a still tender and subdued beat foundation, contrasting this innate darkness with a playful, friendly and uplifting synth motif which makes itself at home right in the very center of every punters heart.

The title cut that is „Retrograde“ provides more of a muscular and well distinct dancefloor cut, drawing influences both from skeletal TechHouse as well as MinimalTechno whilst pairing a spatial, scintillating and ever changing synth melody with subdued, yet ever present muscular low end to a well hypnotic and time dissolving effect.

Finally, the closing tune „Lights“ indulges in futuristic, perfectly sculpted contemporary TechHouse sounds with its tense, ever evolving elements flickering in the dim neon lights of underground venues like reflections on polished chrome, providing a well thrilling setting for club nights and future movie scores alike.
title: Eins Tiefer

description:
Coming in for a next one to be released via Upon.You Records we've got a fresh collaboration going on which sees two long standing and beloved figures of the German scene joining forces to cook up some dancefloor goodness for post-pandemic times. We're talking Kotelett & Sascha Cawa here who are presenting their conjunctional label debut that is „Akemie" with two original tracks and a dubbed out retake of the title cut.

With „Akemie" we see Kotelett & Sascha Cawa provide a deep and highly fascinating dancefloor banger, pairing a precisely sculpted TechHouse foundation with a well hypnotic, slightly modulated main motif accompanied by an evergrowing stack of intertwined, corresponding synth layers leading towards the most angelic widescreen panorama breakdown you'll experience on a large scale P.A. system this year.

Subsequently „Takeshi" is shifting gears and enters full throttle mode whilst the prolific duo navigates a brooding, well futuristic sonic realm, firing up dancefloors with a clean cut, more muscular and surely spine-tingling, Techno-leaning sound vision balancing the thin line between a looming apocalypse and an oncoming salvation, perfectly represented by the tunes glistening melodies.

Finally, the title track makes a second appearance in its so-called „Akemie *Dub" version, providing an even deeper and slightly moodier variation for extended (Neo)Trance-oriented after hours sets and open air sunrise sessions under immaculate skies for a closing.
title: Kotelett & Sascha Cawa

description:
Four single releases within a four years period. If this is what makes an artist a pillar of a labels roster Vienna-based artist T Raum has officially reached this status with „Evil" which is his latest EP on Upon.You Records and our first transmission for the year 2k21.

Opening with „Get Ready" T Raum is sending a clear signal to anyone preparing for things to come on future dancefloors which are, at least according to this furious entree, about to be jam-packed with bodies moving along to brooding, relentless and well eerie Techno grooves revolving around a busy midrange synth, hefty snare attacks and warped vocal transmissions from the outerworld.

Getting loads of „Recognition" is what the second tune on this four tracker deserves due to its cold and tripping, sci-fi and slightly psychedelic TechHouse vibe paired with emulations of icy winds being blown over from exoterrestrial plains, ever morphing modulation sequences and, once again, disembodied vocal bits drilling deep down into the human subconscious.

Furthermore „Evil" lurks within the title track which caters a deep, stripped down and masterly crafted take on spaced out Acid minimalism structurally reminiscent of a vibe brought to us by many mid- and early 90s classics before an intense, swirling, psyched out and siren'esque synth layer starts to drift, wobble and morph through the stereo field for additional braincell stimulation.

And finally there is „Breath Control" - a reference to these strange times we're living in titlewise, catering a musical menu comprised of a dark and claustrophic 2k21-reinterpretation of minimalistic Shuffle Techno garnished with more hypercold sci-fi vibes, spine-tingling sample abuse and ever shifting - and phase-shifting - movements of micro-motifs within the stereo field, adding additional depths to devastating klaxon'esque synth signals and what seems to be an out of the loop metronome playing an essential role in this sonic trip through space and time.
title: T Raum - Evil

description:
Marco Resmann - Past Future (Mini LP)

Coming in as a final transmission from the Upon.You Records camp in 2k20 and a definitive statement straight from the studio of the labels creative mastermind Marco Resmann is his new seven track mini album „Past / Future“.

Inspired by and entirely crafted throughout the COVID-19 induced lockdown that held, and still holds, the entire nightlife industry captive alongside big parts of the music business both facing massive losses with a certainly uncertain future ahead the tracks on „Past / Future“ both reminisce and reflect about the state of an entire scene, how it used to and how – if, when and whenever... – it will be at a point humanity has overcome the global pandemic.

„Past / Future“ is Marco Resmann's musical statement at the end of a strange year in which electronic music was bereft of its natural habitat, dancefloor functionality was rendered redundant and forcefully displaced to a new reality of home- and headphone consumption and streaming sets.

Opening with „Save The Night“ for an intro the Berlin-based producer weighs in a clear message, repeated over and over again by various warped and twisted voices backed by soft, organic and somewhat dubbed out 4/4 foundation providing us with a memory of what once used to be.

The title cut „Past / Future“ featuring vocalist Tony Philips draws inspiration from both deepest DubTechno realms and track'ish, raw and ever filtered (Deep)House rhythm signatures for extended late night sessions whilst paying homage to the long, ever meandering tracks and structures filed under the flag of Intelligent Techno back in the days.


„Nevertheless“ sees Marco Resmann shifting gears to reach full on dancefloor mode, once again amalgamating a driving, yet stripped down and expertly filtered uptempo TechHouse vibe with a wide variety of DubTechno-leaning elements whilst opening up large scale realms with the tunes' beautifully hypnotic main synth line.
Riding the „Wave“ Marco Resmann explores a highly futuristic Sci-Fi Ambient realm of cold, score'esque qualities, fusing the vastness of deep space with warped modular bleeps and echoes of echoes of the Berlin School / ProtoAmbient movement with its histroy harking way back to the 70s even.

„Lost In Space“ is an excursion into the grey area bordering Broken Techno, Electro, Post- Dubstep and various incarnations of Bass Music in general, all glued together by a highly seductive swing, mutated scratches and raw, overwhelming vintage bass waves which turn this one into a timeless future classic within seconds.

The subsequent „Exit“ follows with even more swirling raw vintage bass greatness, backed by a seductive TechHouse groove, ever tweaked high frequency feedbacks and beautiful harmonies, all leading towards a lively, captiving main motif ready to take, at this time: imaginery, dancefloors by storm in combination with the tunes Trance-influenced string and pad sections.

Finally „Belief“ embarks on a journey towards a faint, yet existing silver lining at the horizon with its bubbly, ever sparkling synth cascades and emotionally touching chords backed by what is best to be described as the love child of TechHouse and (Neo)Trance for a closing.
title: Marco Resmann - Past Future (Mini LP)

description:
It's been a while since we had a release on Discobelle from an artist of our native Sweden, that's all about to change with the release of this huge new single from Swedish electronic pop duo @caotico. 

"Gone" showcases a new direction for Caotico, a massive track leaning heavily towards a pulsating UK garage beat that's interspersed with robotic vocals making this a dancefloor bomb, the club edit makes that even more certain and should be your next weapon of choice. 

Fellow Swedes @franskild churns out a housey remix thick with Scandinavian melancholia, the vocals are turned into a haunting affair all while the deep beat is sprinkled with hi-hats and desolate bleeps. 

Toronto outfit @RYMEonRYME rides high on their streak of bumping house/techno tracks with this steadfast remix on which they replace most of the vocals with a single echoed yelp and transplants the track with the help of cinematic synths into more of a 6AM jam for all you late night revelers out there.
title: Caotico - Gone

Noah Gibson returns with a different and more reflective atmosphere. Standing at one point at the dawn of a bright tomorrow: new life. Paired with a technologically backlashed futuristic city scape: piles of illuminated displays, desolate buildings that stand tall as a symbol of a former glory. ‘Krasch 3’ is a scenery with different takes on the same theme.

‘Edge of Tomorrow’, ‘Emerge’ and ‘Route I’ symbolize the brightness where ‘City Entrance’, ‘Backstreet’ and ‘Route II’ brings us a dystopian vision of the next tomorrow.

What we have is a solid return. Noah Gibson brings something new and exciting, something that Krasch Records stands for."

"Grindr", Material object's other contribution, takes us to the wild edge of sonic exploration and back again. Music poised to push us into the abyss with acidic snarls and overwhelming drones, a writhing black sea swallowing everything in it's path.

description:
A1: Savas Pascalidis - Distant Dreams
A2: Savas Pascalidis - Resonate (Echologist Cover Mix)
B1: Savas Pascalidis - Resonate
B2: Savas Pascalidis - Subminimal

Savas Pascalidis releases heavy new EP ‘Brain Waves’ on Atrophic Society
 
Savas Pascalidis is an artist who needs little in the way of introduction. Having a career that spans the last 25 years, and releases on a staggering number of great labels (Gigolo Records, Kurbel, Non Series, Mote Evolver, Stockholm LTD, Children of Tommorow, Skudge, Figure and many more), we’re proud to welcome Savas to the Atrophic Society family.

Brain Waves sees further exploration of the techno that defines Savas’ sound. Savage, grooving and dripping in nuance, all four cuts on this EP will set the night on fire.

Distant Dreams is a tunnelling beast that twists and turns over itself with insistent percussive slaps and grooving bass, underpinning a driving synth line that stacks up to create a furious EP opener.

There were no parts to work from to make a remix with, so in a total class move Echologist drops a cover mix of the B1 track Resonate, though it could be said that it’s inspired by all the original tracks on the EP. He strips it back to the bare necessities and propels it forward in true Echologist style.

The original of Resonate is noisey and blustery as the title would suggest, hissing and bleeping over a mid range bassline that tastefully peaks and troughs for the length of the journey. Finally, rounding out the EP in total class, Subminimal crescendo’s with layers of noise and delay over a funk-fuelled rhythm.

All four tracks on this forward thinking EP for Atrophic Society are essential machine-made music and an outstanding addition to Savas’ body of work.

Mastered by Tim Xavier at Manmade Mastering
Distributed by Diamonds and Pearls
Atrophic Society 009 Copyright © 2017
title: Savas Pascalidis – Brain Waves [AS009]

description:
Gotshell releases dark new EP ‘Quarkcima’ on Atrophic Society.
 
Following releases on Detroit Underground, Nachtstrom Schallplatten, Planet Rhythm and BluePrint Records, Gotshell releases his first EP on Atrophic Society.
 
The Colombian aficionado has been making waves across the world for his uncompromising take on the darker side of techno. His new EP ‘Quarkcima’ is no different, with a thick slice of bass-heavy machine music made for late night body moving.
 
‘Quarkcima’ follows a bleepy lead with layers of bass, building to a satisfying and tasteful crescendo, which steers clear of the tropes and uses frequencies to their fullest. It invokes a dark and foreboding atmosphere like a creeping black fog.
 
First on remix duty is Xhin, who takes the bleepy synth lead and twists it into a heavy-but-funky robotic jam, stark and cold on the surface but with plenty of heat underneath. 
 
Jeff Derringer takes the reins for the second remix, wielding the original parts masterfully into a dense, bassline-driven triplet groove that takes the vibe up a few notches. 
 
Finally, label head Vohkinne adds punch and percussion to his charged and clanging remix, which rounds out a fierce package in style.
 
‘Quarkcima’ is four cuts of essential techno that will never leave your crate.

Mastered by Tim Xavier at Manmade Mastering
Distributed by Diamonds and Pearls
Atrophic Society 008 Copyright © 2017
title: Gotshell – Quarkcima (Incl. Xhin, Jeff Derringer & Vohkinne Rmx's) – AS008

Each track captures a unique set of machine sounds and turns them into brooding, heady, atmospheric techno. A Thousand Cuts and Scythe serve as heavy hitters, whereas Nature Control and Broad Swathe to the Far Side bring a dark mood seething with anticipation.

Atrophic Society regulars Echologist and Vohkinne are joined by new friends DJ Spider and Material Object for the label's first Various Artists release. Kicking things off with his regular sleek touch, Echologist delivers our favourite track of his to date in the aptly titled Splatter Ballistics Cop, with trademark large low end and analog squelches aplenty. DJ Spider follows with a clanking, reverberating behemoth full of dark drones and unsettling background noise entitled Necro Nebula. Material Object Injects his track Wipe Out with supercharged urgency, envoking the kind of late night, Dark, floor burner we're particularly fond of. Label head Vohkinne steps up to the plate again with the sweaty and headstrong 3rd release from Atrophic Society, ‘Creole Rhythm’. It’s concrete rhythm, combined with an analogue lead riff stirs echoes of warehouses, insistently driving forward, mindful of where it’s been. Tripeo remixes the title track with gusto and flair as we’ve come to expect, staying faithful to the riff whilst aggressively re-paving the rhythm, offering a slight twist on the original idea. Rounding out the EP, ‘Be Like the Sun’ removes the rhythm to focus on tone, frequency, shades of sub bass and saturation.

description: Atrophic Society welcomes Brendon Moeller for it's second release, delivering 2 deeply textured and emotive technoscapes. Wielding a warbled bassline and synthetic bleeps with a masters touch, the title track meanders within a natural landscape, fuzzing and washing around descending chirps and following the call of a distant foghorn, leading us through the Passage to Obscurity. Vohkinne takes the delicacies of the original and hammers them into submission, where the original meanders the remix charges, bringing the distant foghorn into focus as a challenging and stubborn lead. Closing out the EP, Contents Under Pressure surges forward with an insistent Bleep, purging and cleansing itself through gnarling bass, never questioning its purpose as it takes you to a higher state.
title: Brendon Moeller - Passage to Obscurity

description:
The debut release for Atrophic Society, home to label founder Vohkinne, is the culmination of years of experimentation with different ideas and aliases. Slithering and raking across heavy groundswells, centering around a whisper and a groan, chanting through the thud of drums and ritualistic rhythms, “Battery” introduces us to Vohkinne’s vision. Different from it’s origin, breeding an atmosphere of deliberate anxiety without fear or compromise, the veteran Ben Sims crafts a clenched fist, unrelenting in purpose. Dark and urgent, both interpretations ring clear through the fog.

Release Date: 19th May 2014
Formats: 12” & Digital
title: Vohkinne - Battery (AS001) Clips

description:
After 10 years Sunchase releases his second LP 'Timeline' on Ukrainian Kashtan

One of Europe's key figures in the drum and bass music scene of the 2000s - Sunchase - returns with his long-awaited album on Kashtan, a newly launched label from Ukraine, on 1st of December 2020.
Kashtan arises with the release of the renowned Ukrainian producer Sunchase, aka Alexander Pavlenko, whose debut album, 'Static Nitro', came out on Drone Audio in 2010. Sunchase had numerous singles on such cult labels like Moving Shadow, Metalheadz and Hospital Records and after 10 years he finally returns to the LP format.
His second album 'Timeline', just like the concept of the label, blurs the boundaries between genres of electronic music, and cannot be assigned to any particular style. The melancholic and abstract sounds give off a sense of reclusiveness, with drum and bass rhythms peeking and sometimes breaking through to the surface, yet more often they go deeper, creating room for bass music, dub and even a slight touch of IDM, thus creating a very special state. The album as a whole appears as a voluminous, complete, and aesthetically established piece of work.

Kashtan is a new Ukrainian record label. The primal concept of the label is to discover and to pick carefully gems of Ukrainian electronic music that are not defined and limited by genre definitions. The selection focuses on pure creativity, aiming for the listener to return again and again, despite shifts in trends and time. It was created and developed by Vera Logdanidi, a Kyiv-based producer and DJ, one of the founders of the Rhythm Büro project. Vera has been hosting a radio show on the waves of Kyiv's independent project 20ft Radio for over three years now. The show consists mainly of unreleased tracks by Ukrainian electronic producers. Kashtan assists in presenting not very known musicians to a global audience and places them on the same level with already established producers, whilst also revealing their creative personalities. The community that is quickly forming around Kashtan is constantly replenished with new blood and fresh ideas where musicians exchange personal experiences and ideas.
The releases of Kashtan will be executed in a rather unusual format: it will be a limited series of collectible packs, including a USB stick with music and additional multimedia content, as well as other materials. These packs can later be collected into a catalog. Also, the LP will be released digitally on Kashtan's Bandcamp page and all other known online stores.

Follow Sunchase on Facebook > facebook.com/sunchase.ua
Follow Sunchase on Instagram > instagram.com/nanich_sunchase/
Label : @kashtan_ukraine
title: Sunchase - Timeline LP [ Kashtan 001 ]

description:
Rhythm Büro’s fourth release is a much anticipated EP from one of it's co-cofounders, Na Nich aka Alexander Pavlenko. Pavlenko has been making music for nearly 20 years, most notably under the alias Sunchase. With the latter project, he was known in the drum and bass world as something of a child prodigy, but more recently Pavlenko started applying his artistry towards soundscapes that can be filed into the techno category. In the last four years he’s been first and foremost involved with Rhythm Büro, a techno initiative, party series and label from Kiev, Ukraine, that has since become well-regarded among DJs and dancers internationally.

This EP marks Na Nich's first solo EP, following a track featured on Semantica Records’ anniversary compilation ‘Arquitectura del Sueño’, along with a few tracks appearing on Rhythm Büro’s previous VA releases.

RB004 opens on the A1 with a track entitled ‘The Key’ which is one of the first tracks made by Na Nich. The listener is gently introduced to an ambient wonder wall before some percussive elements open up and synths set the mood: a transportive journey led by a kalimba-infused melody which swells with a certain ambiguity that seems to lend a shamanistic touch. A2’s ‘DVA’ is a more four-to-the-floor dubbed-out gentle fist pumper, with melting synth melodies and foggy layers backdropped by steady reaching high-hats and a consistently wise kick drum. A strong element of the psychedelic and inquisitive is much present.

The B side of the record is another part of the story: B1's ‘Log’ is an epic night-finisher dreamscape, a strong element of space seems to be the focus here as beats play less present in this foggy cinematic soundtrack to a film that has yet to be made. The remix version by Luigi Tozzi on B2 reminds us how deep this prolific Italian artist can take us down the rabbit hole. For fans of danceable, groove-centered and though provoking tunes to loose one's and find one's mind to.
title: Na Nich - The Key EP [ Rhythm Büro 004 ]

description: The tenth 22:22 release sees Sunchase preseting us with another EP of proper drum'n'bass goodness. This time Alexander showcases a familiar darker side of his production with a bunch of smashing rollers. Uncompromising sound and crystal clear production makes Slap EP a lethal dancefloor weapon you shouldn't miss. Trademark techy aesthetics, groovy vibes and intricate break sampling bring out the best the genre has to offer in a distinct unique way only Sunchase is able to deliver. Venues around the continent are getting ready for this one as the release definitely will take its rightful place inside top DJ's playlists.
title: Sunchase - Slap EP

description:
It's springtime and 22:22 is back with a bunch of sunny vibes! This time it's the label boss himself - Sunchase, who delivers this three track EP of juicy beats. While Alexander is busy exploring different genres in recent times, this release is a perfect reminder of that he is still one of the finest breakbeat masters in eastern Europe.

So Sweet wastes no time to get you started on the positive vibrations with its tight drums and flowing bassline. Double bass and trademark percussion sounds add a nice touch of warmth to the groove. It's just like the lady sings - so sweet when he starts rhythm!

When We Are Alone is pure love. Lush chords, intricate break work and deep bass touch your soul in a way only Sunchase's drum'n'bass can do. It's an elegant and intimate vibe that makes your body move just as well, so expect to hear this at lots of venues around the world very soon.

Why Are We Here mysterious and hypnotizing nature grabs your attention immediately and does not let go until the very end putting you into a sweet state of wonder. This piece retains its edginess without losing any depth and attention to detail, which is no mean feat and is definitely a worthy addition to any playlist.
title: When We Are Alone EP

Infos :

Faces Records proudly presents "Cross Section", the debut album of  Kez YM, the Berlin based japanese producer.
It's been a long way since  his debut EP at 4Lux Recordings was played by Moodyman back in 2008. Since then he also received support from influential people like Theo Parrish, Rick Wade and Cassy, just to name a few.
Strongly rooted on his Detroit/Chicago Deep House/Funk/Disco/Afro he rocks dancefloors from Berlin to Tokyo, and he's one of the current leading deep house dj's from Japan.
From downbeat to more uptempo tracks, this album is a perfect extension of Kez's path until now. Classy and lustful synths pave the way for a combination of elements that draw inspiration from his jazz masters, his motorcity heroes and a strong percusssive connection to Africa.
You know what? Just let yourself go and enjoy the ride.

All tracks written & produced by Kazuki Yamaguchi.
Mastered by Ugly Drums.
Artwork by Superscript²

Executive Producer : Pablo Valentino for FACES Records Ltd.

Infos : 
Le Sampler Des Copains (litteraly, "The Friends Sampler", in french) is a 10 tracks, 2xLP bundle,
showcasing both established and upcoming talents who currently gravitate around the FACES Records family.
Remember Danilo Plessow first full length offering (even before his MCDE project, when he was producing under the Inverse Cinematics moniker),
or Mono/Poly debut 12", "The George Machine EP"? FACES allowed those then-newcomers, soon to be stars to release their first pieces of wax, because that’s what the label’s all about.
This time we're happy and thrilled to present you a sick draft of new talents’ and friends’ music, ranging from Deep House to Techno, without forgetting the Hip Hop, Instrumental roots.

Friends? All producers on this compilation are close personal friends, old and new.
A Sampler? This 10-tracks selection will give you a taste of what's the future sound ventures of FACES will be about (As a matter of fact S3A, Roman Rauch, Hugo LX, LB aka LABAT, Steven Wobblejay and Pablo Valentino are all working on new material for the label)

Recommended to any Children Of The Drum, beatsmiths, and any repepetitive beats lovers!

B2. Ugly Drums "Hands" feat. :brownstudy

Infos :

Cologne based lone ranger, producer, coffee drinker and occasional bike rider Steffen Baldo aka Ugly Drums has been fine tuning the spokes of his career for 10 hard working years.

Making early marks in the scene with his "Next Room EP" on German based label Polyfon, which received support from Moodymann, MCDE and cemented his reputation early on. Steffen later released dance floor workouts on Rush Hour, Fifty Fathoms Deep, Black Key Records, Quintessential and KOLOR LTD.
His 2013 album left a burning mark on the sample based house scene, pushing the boundaries of the melting pot of his home base Cologne.
Mr Drums has also extensively backed up his original works by remixing the likes of Manuel Tur, Toby Tobias, Holly Backler, Andy Ash, Inkswel and Bartellow.

After the smashing "Get Up" edit released on FACES alongside Kid Sublime and Jayson Brothers, Ugly Drums is back on FACES Records with his best work yet- "The Freak EP"! Co-produced by Kalakuta Soul System, Chesney and featuring Detroit based MC/Producer :brownstudy, Steffen deliver a multi dimensional, raw, untainted EP, that displays a splash of all colours- House, Disco and Hip Hop. A definitive weapon for the record crate! 

2014 FACES Records Ltd. All Rights reserved

description:
Starting his musical journey at itch fm with UK Veteran Disorda in 2001, Ghost went on to host his own radio show for 5 years in a time considered a golden era for UK Hip Hop. In 2003 Ghost released his first record, the 'Ghost Stories EP'. Over the next 6 years followed 4 videos, 3 albums Seldom Seen often Heard (2006), ‘Freedom of Thought’ (2009), ‘Postcards From The Edge’ (2011), 4 EP's, a 7" single, a mix CD, guest production and remix work for the likes of Verb T, Kashmere (Strange U), Bonobo, The Heavy, Nicole Willis and the Soul Investigators. 

Ghost is one of a handful of UK artists to have his music licensed in Japan; this led to 2 album releases for Japanese markets only.
New album 'Shards of Memories' marks the 10 year anniversary since the release of Ghost’s critically acclaimed debut album ‘Seldom Seen Often Heard’.

Over the years Ghost has carved out a sound which is very much his own, thoughtful emotive laden Hip Hop beats and Instrumentals. Not just loops but heavily composed arrangements drawing the listener in to the music, multiple listens are required to hear everything that’s going on. On ‘Shards’ Ghost continues his own journey with a mix of past and contemporary Hip Hop sounds, live instrumentation, a hint of orchestral and blues vibes. Ghost has pulled together another masterful soundtrack. The key focus was to give the listener a journey through the album. This isn’t a mish mash of guest features that don't work as a collection of music. An album is a true test of any artist; an album takes time, planning and patience. And creativity.

‘Shards of Memories’ features the cream of UK Rap including Cappo, Verb T, Joker Starr, Benny Diction, Kal Sereousz and Efeks. It features two of Dublin’s finest in G.I. and Lethal Dialect, plus Australian legend Brad Strut and Aeryz from NZ. In keeping with a Ghost tradition the album also features 3 instrumental tracks, a style which earned Ghost much praise for his mostly instrumental 2nd album 'Freedom of Thought'.

To make the project even more unique Ghost created all 3 music videos by himself to mark this 10 year anniversary. Cutting his teeth making the ‘Prawns’ music video for Dirty Dike’s recent album and videos for Aussie heavyweight Briggs, Ghost show’s his creative side extends beyond music, now a talented director, cameraman and editor working as a freelance Creative Video Production freelancer.

The track Reflect features the voice of Ustad Amir Khan talking in an All India Radio documentary. Poem features the voice of Zareef Ahmed.

description:
Amselcom is the home for my own music and some of my favourite artists. Digging now even deeper into the past of the musical journey of this label gave me a better insight, how music can transform and evolve through time. I happily re-discovered some tracks that I once loved but forgot and even discovered some new ones.

The practice of selecting songs and curating this third compilation made me realise once more, how unique each musical piece is by itself. The diversity of sounds within these tracks is almost endless and the more you zoom into a track, the more things you may discover that you never heard there before. Some hidden bleep, rustle or texture that you can only hear if you listen closely, these are the things on a musical journey that totally fascinate me.

Every one of us will have different emotions and memories connected to these songs. Let's revive these feelings and create some new ones at the same time. Let‘s zoom into the present, the place and time where all sounds, feelings and emotions lie.

@klangdruide

Downtown Party Network – Disco Ball Drama
FBR026

A1. Disco Ball Drama
AA1. Keep On Running
AA2. No Drama Afterhours

Vinyl - available from July 11th
Digital - available from July 28th

Downtown Party Network already come with an excellent pedigree of disco licked tunes for quality imprints like Eskimo, Is It Balearic? Recordings and Dirt Crew. And so the debut appearance on Futureboogie seems like a most comfortable fit, with the ‘Disco Ball Drama’ extended player providing three shining examples of delicious grooves.

Title cut, ‘Disco Ball Drama’ cuts a familiar beat with a rolling and gritty acid-like arpeggio, the classy pads smoothing out the rougher edges and providing huge swashes of sunshine moments on this real mid-season winner.

‘Keep On Running’ on the flip side turns out a heads down, boogie-fest, with its elastic bassline, deep Rhodes chords and lively percussion doing the business here.

Closing the release is ‘No Drama Afterhours’, going down the cosmic alley for a slightly deeper cut. Spatial pads and looping syth arps gently collide over the swinging disco drums whilst the bass plays out an infectious melody, one for the ‘afterhours’ indeed.
title: Downtown Party Network - Disco Ball Drama EP [Futureboogie]

In a particularly savagely rained December in 2011 https://soundcloud.com/w-lhelm and I met to do a "live set" for the new year and something about the weather, the hang of the air, our own dire dark personas, and talks of running microphones through bunkers led to this over a few buzzy drearies.

ARTIST @FinestWear
TITLE A Journey
CAT# NT111
STYLE Deep House, Garage

1. Forgiveness
2. Let It Out
3. A Journey
4. How We Roll 
5. The Love You Keep
6. A New Dawn

The London legend Finest Wear returns to NT with a heavy hitting six-track EP. His latest sonic adventure takes the listener on A Journey through his love for all things deep -- sit back and enjoy. 

On his first release of 2021, Finest Wear goes back to his roots. The ep opens with Forgiveness, a deep & moody vocal cut-up with a soulful groove. Let It Out takes you on a trip to those peak-time dancefloor moments lost in the music. One highlight of the ep is A Journey: a lush, chilled-out soundscape built in waves – evolving, peaking and eventually fading like a fine sunset. Beautiful stuff. How We Roll kicks up the tempo with a driving groove and deadly hook, setting things up for the familiar garage vibes of The Love You Keep. Finally closing things out with New Dawn, an old-school track with a tip of the hat to ‘90s Chicago house. 

Blurring the lines between deep house, techno and garage in his productions, Finest Wear is the production moniker of London producer & deejay Cenzo Scoglio. Under his various aliases (Finest Wear, MrCenzo, MididropMusic) Cenzo has releases on BBE, Colour & Pitch, Kolour Recordings, Plastic City, Loudeast, UM Records, and Black Soul to name a few. Among others, he released two projects on Chicago’s legendary Large Music in 2017, which filled the deep house charts and found support from Sebb Junior, Demarkus Lewis, Saison, Nacho Marco and Souldynamic among others.

Past Finest Wear productions for Nordic Trax have been supported by the likes of Crackazat, Joris Voorn, Groove Armada, Danny Tenaglia, Jamie Jones, DJ T, Radio Slave, Franck Roger, John Digweed, Danny Howells, Claptone and many more.

::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

A Journey by Finest Wear is out April 2, 2021

Written & produced by Finest Wear. Published by Nordic Trax (Socan).  Copyright 2021 Nordic Trax

ARTIST Jon Delerious
TITLE Can’t Hold Back
CAT# NT110
STYLE Deep House

1. Can’t Hold Back (Main Mix)
2. Can’t Hold Back (Delerious Dub)
3. Prism
4. Keep It Hot
5. Vibes N Dub

Jon Delerious is back with his first release on the label since the 2018 hit Let’s Work. The Calgary producer goes deep with a five-track ep full of lush vibes and built around Jon’s infectious grooves.

Opening up the release Delerious delivers two feel good mixes of Can’t Hold Back. The title track is a catchy big-room anthem with elements of funk and soul that builds into an uplifting summertime vibe -- perfect for late nights & early mornings. On Prism & Keep It Hot the Canadian producer returns to his West Coast house roots with dub elements, acid basslines and slick percussion. Finally on Vibes N Dub, Delerious slows things down with a chilled-out track reminiscent of the best ‘90s downtempo.

Jon’s last release for Nordic Trax [Let’s Work, NT094] was his best-selling release on the label after 20 years on the scene! The title track reached the deep house Top 20 on Beatport and Traxsource and received widespread support from the likes of Groove Armada, Nick Warren, Kyodai, Jamie Trench, Pawas, Rob Da Bank, Kid Enigma, The Revenge, Giom, Danny Tenaglia and more.

Jon Delerious has six previous EPs on Nordic Trax, as well as the critically-acclaimed album 'No Warning' [2004]. Jon’s dub-influenced house has caught the eye of deejays and tastemakers alike, ending-up perhaps most notably as the lead track on Lee Burridge’s Global Underground compilation. More recently he's released music for Large Music, Tilted, Lost My Dog, Soulstar, Llama Farm and Sidetrak among others.

A native of Calgary, Jon Delerious is a regular on the Western Canadian music scene and has been playing the infamous Shambhala Music festival since its inception. Alongside many club gigs and residencies in his home town, Jon is the 'go-to' dj for touring royalty having opened for everyone from Kevin Saunderson to Ben Watt. He hosts a weekly broadcast from his studio on twitch with a loyal following from around the globe.

::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

Can’t Hold Back by Jon Delerious is out Feb 26, 2021

ARTIST Sean Dimitrie & Tim Fuller
TITLE New Beginnings (feat @JT-Donaldson Remix)
CAT# NT108
STYLE Deep House

1. New Beginnings (JT Donaldson Remix)
2. New Beginnings (Main Mix)
3. New Beginnings (Radio Mix)
4. New Beginnings (Club Organ Edit)

It’s a family affair as three of our favourite artists return to the label with New Beginnings – an uplifting jazzy house track with a powerful message for the times. 

Producer Sean Dimitrie is back on Nordic Trax with vocalist & fellow Vancouverite Tim Fuller. The two have been a part of the Vancouver scene since the ‘90s and have collaborated on some classic tunes for the likes of Bombay, Odori and Salted Music. They recently performed a live PA at our 100th release party where this song first caught our attention. 

With three killer versions from Sean in the can, we dialed-up our old friend JT Donaldson for remix duty. And with the help of bass player Max Gerl & his own skills on the MPC, the Dallas producer took the track to another level: dropping a top-shelf jazzy house workout with an impeccable groove. 

JT Donaldson is one of the finest US house producers of his generation. He has hundreds of producing & writing credits on some seminal labels, including early on Fair Park, Cajual & Aesoteric and later the iconic Large Music, Seasons and Om Records to name a few. In 2000 we released the legendary The Quiet Life EP he produced with Chris Nazuka (NT012), and JT has also graced us with some high quality remixes over the years – including standouts for Gavin Froome & Joe Silva.

Sean’s history with the label runs deep to Vancouver in the mid-90s where he met label head Luke McKeehan and eventually wound up on our very first release in 1997 as Hide’n’Seek! A classically trained jazz guitarist, Sean’s career in music spans over two decades with releases on Deepen Discs, Leaf, Reverberations & more.

::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

ARTIST Marotti
TITLE New Seeds
CAT# NT107
STYLE Deep House

1. New Seeds
2. In Da Beat
3. Broad Sweep

We’re excited to welcome rising producer Marotti to the Nordic Trax family. For his label debut, the French producer and deejay drops New Seeds -- a sensational three-track EP of deep and funky house.

The title track introduces Marotti to the world with a hypnotic groove that gets to work straight out of the gate. New Seeds bumps with swirling chords, a driving bass and an uplifting vocal all floating over a swinging beat. In Da Beat continues the stellar vibe with a deep-rhodes number that rises to the end with lovely key solos. Rounding out the release, Broad Sweep is one for the heads with a dreamy, chilled-out soundscape perfect for late nights & early mornings.

Jean Pierre Marotti, aka Marotti, is originally from Rennes and is of a French and Italian background. He made his way to house music after a dedicated upbringing full of funk, jazz & disco. He’s released on Rutilance Recordings, Stereophonk Records and his own label Meso Records. His work has been supported by Mark Farina, Groove Assassin, Sartorial and more. He recently remixed NT fave Demarkus Lewis for Smashing Trax. Keep an eye out for Marotti and watch the new seeds grow.

::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

All songs written & produced by Jean Pierre Marotti. Published by Nordic Trax (Socan). Copyright 2020 Nordic Trax

ARTIST Chris Udoh
TITLE All The Pieces Fit
CAT# NT106
STYLE Deep House, Deep Tech

1. Everlasting
2. All The Pieces Fit
3. Soft Whisper
4. Quarantine Deep

Philadelphia producer Chris Udoh (Wamdue Kids, Tigerhook) makes his long-overdue return to Nordic Trax with a four-track ep of deep, tech vibes.

The four tracks on All The Pieces Fit follow in the tradition of Chris Udoh’s impeccable production standards -- built and refined over three decades in the scene as a successful producer and deejay. Drifting between big room tech house and deeper, late-night moments, this release will hit all the right notes for the discerning listeners out there.

Originally from St. Louis, it wasn’t until Chris moved to Atlanta and teamed-up with Deep C & Chris Brann as the Wamdue Kids that his recognition grew beyond the Eastern US. The trio toured the circuit and had a string of successful releases on seminal labels Peacefrog, Guidance, Studio !K7 and Nite Grooves to name a few.

Based in Philly since ’96, Chris Udoh’s solo work and collaborations have been equally as prolific as his early Wamdue outings, including stand-out releases on Siesta, Worship, Hooj Chons, Saw Recordings, Shaboom and of course Nordic Trax (Breeze In The Night, 2004). He was a resident of Fabric for several years in the ‘00s (with Deep C as Tigerhook) and remains busy in the studio with remixes and original productions continuing to flow.

Released by:
Nordic Trax
EP release date:
28 August 2020

ARTIST Demarkus Lewis @demarkuslewis
TITLE Emotional Landslide
CAT# NT105
RELEASE May 15, 2020

Demarkus Lewis returns to Nordic Trax with a blazing three-track ep of his signature deep house. In his third outing on the label, the Dallas producer pulls no punches delivering an emotional release of underground goodness.

The three track Emotional Landslide EP features two mixes of the title track; an uplifting groover built around a swinging hook and Demarkus’ airtight drum programming. Amen Buddah follows a driving kick and his signature beats that falls somewhere in between tech house & garage, quite refreshing.

He’s been called "the hardest working man in House" and in 2014 Demarkus Lewis was the #1 Jackin' House Artist on Traxsource. But the term ‘jackin’ doesn’t really do his style justice. The versatile producer is equally known for his deep & soulful excursions, including his stand-out collaboration with vocalist Martha Wash ‘Look To The Light’.

Fans of the label will no doubt be familiar with Demarkus Lewis, he released a pair of high quality eps on Nordic Trax: Make It Mellow (NT031, 2003) & Parallels (NT037, 2004). The Dallas producer has been a staple since he burst on the scene in 1999. His epic discography is jammed with classics on some of the finest labels including Nervous, Kingstreet Sounds, Slip n Slide, Salted, Large Music, Aesoteric, Guesthouse, Doin’ Work and his own label Grin Music.

ARTIST Pete Moss & Onur Özman @petemosstracks @onurozman
TITLE I Can’t Even EP
CAT# NT104
RELEASE February 21, 2020

1. I Can’t Even
2. Colder Hands
3. What I Need

As we kick off 2020 and a new decade of music, our old friend Pete Moss returns to the label on a fresh collaboration with producer Onur Özman. The three-track ep is driven by the outstanding title track – an uplifting deep tech journey with a deadly vocal hook.

Fans of the label will no doubt be familiar with Pete Moss. The Philadelphia deep house don has been producing quality underground music for over two decades, with releases on Ovum, Dessous, Alola, Recline, Kwench, Worship and of course a pair of excellent eps on Nordic Trax (NT045 & NT053). In 2019 his remix of Colette's "Dreams" topped the dj charts and was a massive hit from Berlin to Burning Man. 

Onur Özman’s unique sound is a combination of music and architecture. His music creates soundscapes with atmosphere and function, as he says "with feelings & dance". He has been producing, performing and presenting deep, tech house music worldwide for more than a decade. His diverse discography includes releases for the likes of Noir Music, Rebirth, iRecords and forthcoming on the legendary Yoshitoshi.

Besides his own productions, Onur has collaborated with many renowned artists such as Kyodai, HotSince82, Cari Golden, Kevin Over, Cari Golden, Lazarusman & now Pete Moss. Onur rose originally from the Istanbul house music scene, but is now based in Switzerland.

::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

Pete Moss & Onur Özman - I Can't Even EP is out Feb 21, 2020
